content: This app is the great example about usage of advanced technology for greater good of people in need. Finally received the call today. Someone called me and asked me to verify if there is phone number written on paper he was holding or not. And if there was then read it out loud. I was feeling so much fortunate to be the eyes for someone and it literally fulfilled one of the purpose of my life. GOD BLESS THE DEVELOPERS OF THIS AWESOME APPLICATION.

I like the idea of this app to be able to assist people but the first call I got, the man showed me a package and asked me to tell him what it said and the picture froze in a way that I couldn't see to read it to him. I was able to use my phone still I just couldn't see what he was showing me within the app; I felt terrible that I couldn't assist him. Then the app asked me to review the experience and wouldn't even let me click to review it. I don't think this app works as well as it should.

Love this app, have had it for years now and it's sometimes pretty rare to get a call. I've helped a lady that was visually impaired who herself helped others. They girl she was with was hesitant about using this app so we just talked a little about calls I've helped others on and explained to her that no request would be to small for her to use this. Helped another gentleman bake a cake even lol. Have recommended to all of my friends and family.

Update: happened again 02/11/2022 01/09/2022:"Trying to answer" I had just downloaded the app & was watching the instuctional video when I got a real call. The lady asked me a question & my screen was black & the screen read "trying to answer call" with a blue loading wheel. I was so excited to get to help someone so quickly but so sad that the call video didn't connect. We could hear each other. I just couldn't see anything. Fix this please. Seems like a lot of people are having the same issue.
replyContent: Hi thank you so much for volunteering and for leaving feedback! Sometimes, these issues can be due to poor connection, however, I will bring the issue up with our development team to find a solution. Thanks again, and I hope you will receive another call soon!

content: Love the idea, would be great if they could maybe make a setting like other apps for drivers have where you can make yourself unavailable or available for calls. I always seem to recieve them when I'm driving and feel bad I have to decline.

Terrific idea! I registered on 30th January 2022 and I got a call on 31st January. Absolutely stunning experience. Someone called me to help him with setting the temperature on his oven. While he held the phone near the temperature dial I directed him to show me the up and down arrow by moving his camera and i asked him to go closer to the dial to help. We went back and forth and finally did it in about 2 to 3 minutes. I don't know where he called from nor do I know his name. Great experience!

Not sure why other people have had so much trouble with the app. I have a OnePlus N200 5G phone running on Android 11 OS. Worked gr8
Don't ever get any calls and if I do try to answer it, it says the call went to someone else.

Whatever system they use to reach out to people clearly seems to favor selecting people who have successfully answered calls before. I've received (among their pointless emails talking about other people's success) one email detailing I missed a call (despite receiving no notification). And only had one call in which I stared at a 'connecting' alert for 15 minutes.

content: Great app, here's a tip: I've had the app for over a year and I just found that on Android devices your permissions can be removed from the app if it's not opened every few months. To get around this go into your settings and go to the Be My Eyes app settings, there should be a section for Permissions. Click that and make sure to turn off "remove permissions if app isn't used". This was causing my connection errors and was not allowing me to connect with calls. Hopes this helps!

I've had the app for just under a year and have had about four calls reach my phone. Historically other volunteers have answered more quickly than me, but tonight I was able to help someone "see" the buttons on their dishwasher. Such an easy way to help a fellow human. For those who haven't gotten the chance to be the first to connect, be patient. It's worth it.

I have received 3 calls over the course of 1yr and unfortunately EVERY SINGLE CALL states "trying to connect" I don't mind to sit and wait for the connection but after 10minutes I'm gonna assume it isn't gonna work. Go into your phone settings to Apps and choose "Be My Eyes" click on camera and allow permissions and click on video and allow permissions. I had my first call today and it went great because I was able to help someone with their bank deposit specially after a person behind them was trying to tell them lies about the information on two checks they were depositing. I was not shown any private information but I was able to tell her what she needed and I'm so thankful that I was able to help!!!!!
Used to work in UAE and in Uzbekistan. In USA it just shows the black screen and spinning symbol in the middle, saying ''Connecting'', but doesn't connect
When a call came through, I could hear but couldn't see the person I was to help. For some reaaon, the screen was stuck on 'trying to answer call'. You should look into improving the app.
The idea of this app us great, but the technicality is not. Can't help when it is trying to connect you and fail almost every time. It would be nice if the developers fix this.

App used to work. Now call shows it's trying to connect but never connects fully and shows same circular arrow indicating a connection attempt but it never moves and never connects. Definitely need to invest more in Android app if they actually want to have a global presence.

Great idea, but the app gave me issues when I got a call today. Lost connectivity, couldn't leave feedback after the call, & the audio came through the regular phone, no option for speakerphone. I hope they improve this. Otherwise, it's so cool!

When I downloaded this app years ago, it worked great. But in the last few months I've received 2 calls. One could not connect to video and one couldn't answer the call. Feel frustrated on behalf of the blind. Please fix.
I think you guys need to update this app. Got my first call today but the wheel just spun around and said connecting. It never connected. I went and did a test call again, and no sound.

I have really enjoyed this app but the last two calls I got it wouldn't ever connect. My app, phone and signal is update and strong. I feel like I've let two folks down now because I couldn't help them.
I got several calls but it keeps saying trying to connect, today I heard a voice but it still said trying to connect....y'all need to get this fixed

I love helping people on this app, wish I got more calls!! You have to answer super quick when you get a call or it understandably goes to the next person! It worked great both times I answered the call in time to help.

This app and service is the moral hight of why technology exists and what we as human beings can do for eachother. The ability to reach out and help someone in the most simplest of ways by taking 5 minutes of your time is beautiful.

I tried to open a call and the message said only iPhones and iPads were available to answer. When I looked at the app download, it said I could answer using an Android. I hope the person got their situation figured out ðŸ¤·â€â™€ï¸

I really love the concept of this app. However, the last couple of times I've gotten a call, the screen was blank and said "Connecting" even though I could hear the person, and so I was unable to help them. :(
Cool concept but 3 calls with issues, 1st no visual only sounds last 2 would not connect. Do better.
replyContent: Hi, we apologize for any issue you might be having! Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our customer support at info@bemyeyes.com? We'll try and get the problem fixed as soon as possible.

content: I really love this idea, but the past three calls I've received the app just wouldn't pick up the call. I accept the call and it freezes up.
Same issue as everyone else, went to answer a call today and it wouldn't connect. I love the idea of this app but it def needs upgradesq

This app is really cool. It's always good to use technology for helping others. Below are some suggestions from me (not sure if y'all already implemented it or not): 1. Rating system of the helpers. The goal is just to avoid crazy ppl trying to trap or do any non beneficial things to the blind people. 2. Maybe the app can also connect blind people to their nearest people around them. That way, if they need a direction, someone nearby can easily help navigating it.

This has been a GREAT experience. The app requires minimal information (name and email) and doesn't require any interaction until you recieve a call. If I cant answer, the call goes to the next volunteer. My interactions have felt professional, and actually quite fascinating. It's made me stop and consider the things that I take for granted every day. Worth your time!

Signed up yesterday evening after my daughter told me about the app..just had my 1st call, less than 24 hrs later. What an awesome experience, even if it was just telling them what color something was. It pleases me to be able to help just that little bit more in my free time. Amazing, good job creating this! Something so simple helps so much :)

There needs to be more guidance apps like this to help disabled people. If you're visually impaired, there are people ready to help. In my opinion people should be vetted before volunteering just to prevent abuse. But that's my only concern. For those not getting any calls, it took me 3 months, its normal as theres millions of helpers and only hundreds of thousands impaired people

I'm a low vision therapist and found this app because 2 total blind patients were scheduled so I wanted to be prepared to provide more than what is available for patients with low vision. I tried it, a volunteer quickly answered. We were both new to using the app but she was a great help to me. I will know how to guide all of my patients on how to use and what to expect. Thanks to all the volunteers and to the developer. I'll spread the word very quickly about this app.
Great app that connects people in need with people who want to help without it being a burden on either end. Clean looking app with no extra info clogging up the page.
First call right out of the gate the video didn't connect. Not sure whose side the issue was on but they had to try again. Disappointing and frustrating for both.

great app. its so easy to help others and it doesn't take alot of time. even if it did, it's really satisfying helping someone. for example, help them choose or pick out their preferred color of shirt or sort cash, understand directions on a vending machine for example. the calls I've taken last about 20 seconds. its so great to know that there are 15 times the number of volunteers vs the number of blind people using the app. I actually wish I would receive more calls.

Just tried to help someone and the video connection could not be established. Heard them just fine but couldn't do anything else. Felt really bad I couldn't help them. I have full bar strength signal.
Fantastic. Brilliant UI. Easy to use, easy to help. And such a thoughtful and useful concept. This should be up there as a #1 installed app!

Although there are a few small tweaks that could make this app better, overall this is a great app. This app is all about helping others that are visually impaired. There are no ads, it's free. It's just to help others. It has a small footprint on your phone and runs unnoticed until someone needs help. Give it a try and be the eyes for someone. I have it on my phone so I know that it works without hurting or slowing down your phone.

Great idea and glad to see that the volunteer to user ratio is very high. Unfortunately, I had to delete it instantly for a big reason. I work 12 hour overnight shifts, so I'm actually awake at night and asleep during the day. The app states it automatically assigns a call accepting window to daytime only hours based on your timezone and there's no way to change it. I'd love to at least be able to edit my time zone to trick the app into calling me at night.

I so love the principle and the idea behind this app. I keep it to assist others when in need. Nonetheless, I can hardly ever answer calls because the button to do so is unresponsive when tapped. Just today, after years of being registered and available in the app, I was able to answer a call but then the audio was so incredibly faint that I had to end up guessing what the person needed and what they were saying. Please evaluate these issues as possible bugs to fix or enhancements to consider.

I LOVE this app in concept. But both calls I've had in several months, there were technical uses. ðŸ˜• Once, the video wouldn't work, so I couldn't help them. The second time, the call dropped. I also wasnt able to help. There's no way to reconnect with them, and i don't know how to get help from the developer, to figure out if there's something wrong with my app.

What an awesome concept! It just keeps getting better with updates. Now, I want to address the one star reviews. I am really sorry you guys are upset that you haven't gotten a call, but that doesn't make this app "pointless". ugh, it is helping so many non or partially sighted people. If you came to this app hoping you'd get your regular dose of warm and fuzzies off the backs of blind people, you're mistaken. This app was made to help people and it is helping.

What a beautiful app. Not sure how else to put it. It's an amazing feeling to help someone in need, big or small. I got my first call after 1 day and the gentleman needed help sorting some bills that he had gotten out of sort. It was a pretty quick call, you can tell they're needing help. They need something from you and you get something in return - that great feeling of connecting & helping. The app works great, very simple to use and that's it.
This app doesn't work on Android. I was able to answer a call but could not see video. Please fix the app so I can actually use it to help someone. I felt so useless.
I am unable to connect when I receive a call. I don't know why, it just say trying to connect. But never connect. Very disappointing ðŸ˜ž

Truly an incredible use of technology. I've had the app since it launched in 2017 & I've had the pleasure of answering about 5 calls as a volunteer. I've received more calls than that but I didn't always answer quick enough so the calls went to someone else. I've helped people read instructions, identify colors, & give directions. The calls are usually quick but they are always the highlight of my day. It feels good to help others & reminds me to be grateful for things I often take for granted.

Amazing idea but the app has some bugs and technical issues. The camera quality is not good enough to help with tasks such as assistance in reading. I also recommend that a sighted person help set up the initial placement of the camera and place some sort of indicator that the callers use to know where to place a document (for assistance in reading mail, for example) so that it can be of a legible distance and position from the camera.

Sounds like a good app. I was hoping to help people who are not able to see. Had the app for 3 months, had 2 calls come in and as soon as I accepted the video disconnected. Maybe too many volunteers but the app is taking space on my phone. Really of no use to me if the video calls disconnect as soon as I try to accept. Deleted the app. Good luck to the rest of you. Maybe you'll have better luck.
replyContent: Hello Richard, thank you for the support. You are right, with more than 3 million volunteers, it takes time to get a call. You can help spread the word about Be My Eyes or accessibility in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users!

content: people keep complaining about not getting calls but,,, thats not the point. just wait until you're needed. it doesn't take much storage so its no biggie. i think its a cool app for blind people (hopefully it works well??) and it would take much time to answer a call for someone, so why not?

idea is great!! but doesn't work for my Android phone. so far I got 4 calls and all the calls had technical issues. my first two calls I couldn't connect because upon answering the call (immediately) I got an error saying sorry couldn't connect. third time I was able to hear a person s voice but his video kept loading. 4th time even after answering the call the screen was just blank..no voice/video. p.s. all the time I was on good 4g network so this was no network issue from my end.

i have a suggestion: on the homepage add a button for volunteers to turn on and off "availability", so that way if you're not currently available to be called- the caller doesn't waste time trying to call you and it automatically connects them to someone who has their "availability switch" turned on.

As with other recent reviewers, wonderful concept with subpar execution on my phone (Pixel 4a). Maybe there's a bug that's currently causing so many calls to be fail to connect. Feels horrible to get so excited to help someone only to have to tell them you can't see their video and can't help them. Would love to give a 5 star review if the bug is fixed!

Love the concept & would love to help but I had this installed for 6 mo. , nothing happened. I shared the app with around 100 people inc. those who are visually impaired. They never used it either. Consider advertising to those that need it. I know this may cost $$ & time but if you want this great concept to work, people have to use it. It'd be easy to email the States Schools for the Blind, Social Media groups for the blind, etc. Other reviewers had the same problem. I'll get a list if needed
replyContent: Hello Kea, thank you for the support! It might take some time to get a call. We do reach out to blind organisations regularly and always try to reach out to more blind and low vision users locally. You are more than welcome to spread the word about Be My Eyes in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users!

content: I didn't get an experience. My phone rang, I was super excited, and hit accept. It then told me that I wasn't logged in, and can't accept calls if I'm not logged in (which I can accept and am sure is a minor fix) however, when I opened the app, I waited a LONG time with the blue circle trying to do its thing. I am going to Uninstaller and try to reinstall again, hopefully it will work next time.

This is a great app in concept but I've been a member for months now without a single call. It's basically a useless app sitting on my phone taking up space. There should be an option to choose availability as well. I work nights so I could be available says and nights on certain days. I'll keep the app for a little longer but if I get over 6 months with no use I'm deleting. EDIT 1/29/20 It has been over a year now with no call. Useless and takes up space.
replyContent: Hello, since we have 3+ million volunteers, it might take time to get a call. All we can ask for is your patience, we hope you will catch a call quite soon. In the meantime you can help spread the word about Be My Eyes in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users!

content: I dl'd this app ~1-2 years ago (I don't remember how long it's been, now..). So far, I've had a few different people call me, and I've enjoyed a quick and pleasant conversation helping people who are blind to read what instructions are being displayed on their computers, or on some other random item or situation where there's no braille/audio available for them. Every time I helped them quickly and easily; and, was left feeling a sense of fulfillment. Get this app and feel good about yourself!

I figured out that you have to align the camera with the object in question. Be my Eyes is very helpful. I recomend this app for blind users who need to know what color things are, what type of food something is, or what a sign says. Be my eyes simply uses kind volinteers to help blind users figure out what they need to know. So, I think Be my eyes is a great app.

I received my first call as a volunteer for Be My Eyes yesterday after having the ap installed for several months. The ap is very simple and I was able to answer and assist the person with their task, reading labels. The biggest thing to improve this ap would be more people using it, especially those who are visually impaired, so that it can help more people.

Awesome service! I tried this out with my blind friend. She was thrilled how easy it was to use from her smart phone, wirh "voice over" comnands. I had someone read fine print on a cleaning product (I couldn't read it, even wirh my glasses), my blind friend got help telling the difference between two similar shaped travel-sive squeeze bottles of toiletries. We were both very impressed!
I love the concept of this app, I just wish there was a way to set what hours I'm available, cuz I only seem to get calls when I'm at work and I always have to ignore them.

This app is a great idea and perfectly executed. For blind users this is great and there's so much help instantly at your fingertips. No long waits in ques for help just instantly answered. However for volunteers I don't suggest at this time downloading this app at this time because there's 2.5 million volunteers and only 137k blind looking for help. So many people want to help that it could be weeks or months before you get one call.

I logged in with my Google account very easily and was able to make my first call within a minute. The volunteer was a real person and was able to assist me with answering the question I had. There were some issues with audio. If you log in and choose to be a volunteer first then it might not do this but I selected to test the need assistance option first, and now it will not let me choose to be a volunteer?

I have had 2 calls in the last 2-3 months that were MUCH BETTER than the calls I had last year. Connection, video, and audio has been updated within the app and the experience has been much better than in previous year (I've had the app for two years). Users have been better too (had a couple creepers last year)-- kind, appreciative, polite.

The app is awesome. It connects the vision impaired with a volunteer that can help with everyday tasks as simple as reading a return address on an envelope to choosing between which can is the tomato soup. Whatever the need it is an amazing way for people to help people.

Amazing - but talking to a blind friend of mine mine uses this app, I feel like a feedback feature may be needed? He has said that he has encountered a handful of people that were not helpful. I think it would be nice for people to be able to choose to not be matched with certain people again or to be more likely to be matched with others. Maybe this has been considered and it's not the best option or maybe the need to volunteer ratio is so different that it's just not an issue.. just a thought!

This app is amazing in theory, but volunteers need a do not disturb setting for off hours when they're either sleeping or not available. That would also cut back on the amount of users you'd need to ping at one time. Four stars until something like that is implemented.

I've only gotten 4 calls since installing the app a year or two ago. There are so many volunteers, that's probably normal, but I still make a point to try and open the app once each day. Regardless of what the developers say, I suspect sometimes my phone's battery-saving settings can get in the way of it running in the background. If you never get any calls ever, try that.

I just answered my first call and I was able to help them get their oven to the correct temperature even with a mostly blurry view. At the end, the app asks if the call had problems or was good. I tried to select that I had problems to report the fuzzy picture, but it didn't do anything after numerous attempts to select it. It immediately selected good when I touched it.

I just started using be my eyes. And is a fantastic application. I cannot believe the people that donate their time to provide such a service. I however do have a suggestion or 2 to improve the service. It would be fantastic if a volunteer would be able to tap on their screen to indicate where an item might be from a certain distance say for example I am looking for a bench. If they were to tap on the screen where the bench is then I would have a good general direction of where the item is.

I am so glad this service exists, and have been anxiously awaiting my first call. When it rang, I clicked the button to connect but it would never connect. I felt terrible because I knew someone on the other end of the line needed help and I was unable to provide assistance. I hope they were able to connect with another volunteer.

Want to give it more but the calls just don't always connect .Have been able to attempt to help someone with a video game. Unfortunately I have had two calls that never connect. Really hope that they were able to get help. Is the a que that people go into to recover help. Just curious.

This is a great app. I'm a new volunteer and the man I helped with my first (and only call so far) was extremely grateful I could help him. He said even though the questions and needs may seem small they are a big deal to the blind community. It was also fun to have a short chat with him; someone who lives on the other side of the country from me but quickly didn't feel like a stranger at all.

So far I have only assisted 1 person, but I think I got just as much out of the interaction as the person I was assisting. This is innovative and integral to the type of ideas we as a species need champion for the betterment of humanity as a whole. This is the way forward and I hope anyone who reads this will also understand the importance. Thank you to the developers that brought this the world

*Check authorizations in app settings* The authorization for the camera in the app may need revoked automatically, as well as the microphone if unused for too long. Considering i get one call every few months, i have missed several opportunities to answer a call because my camera wouldn't open on the app. It would be nice if there was a disclaimer to check permissions and make sure they aren't auto revoked with inactivity. That's all

This is such a personally rewarding and useful app. It provides an invaluable service for sight impaired individuals. As of writing this, I've answered three calls. To be able to literally, be the eyes for another individual that cannot see, is many, many times more rewarding!!!
The visuals never came through on my first call and on my second it was stuck on "trying to answer call" and never successfully connected.

Video did not work. I got my 1st call and was over the moon excited until I realized that the video never turned on. I could hear the person but the screen was totally black. I feel awful that I wasn't able to help and REALLY hope I get another chance &that it will work next time. It took about 4 months for me to recieve my 1st call so I'm really sad it did not work. PLEASE look into that because it is also inconvenient for the person needing help.
replyContent: Hello Misty, we apologise for the issue you are having and we appreciate the feedback. You are welcome to reach our tech support from info@bemyeyes.com whenever you face another issue!

content: Probably the best app on my phone. Have had this app for a few months and only been contacted 3 times. But, what a rewarding experience. On one call I helped a man set the temp on his thermostat. Quick and easy. It must be a god send for those who are visually impaired.

I was skeptical about this app. I installed it yesterday and received my first call this morning. It went very smoothly and the lady I spoke to needed fashion help. "Which looks better..." She was very appreciative and said Thank you several times. Great app!

App conflicts with Bluetooth connections. Seems to act as an always-on audio source, which among other things means that you can't pair with more than one device. Will happily install again when that is fixed, but it unfortunately means that it doesn't work for me in the current version.

I would appreciate more clarity regarding the sound settings. The app does not seem to communicate any sound to my bluetooth headset, so I'm not sure if I should accept a call if it comes up when I'm on my bluetooth. I've also had to reject a call when I was watching YouTube, because the notification banner prevents me from pausing the video, and YouTube will sometimes switch to PIP mode in cases like that.

I've been a helper since 2018, but unfortunately had not been able to answer many calls. Today while reactivating the app on my new phone I immediately received a call. The video and audio quality isn't amazing (could have been the cell network) but with careful communication we were able to successfully get what we needed done. Complaints on quality cannot be immediately blamed on the app, as different areas have different service speeds and qualities.

I am a volunteer - I received a call for the first time today, and I answered, but it never connected with anyone. I wanted to try to find information, maybe I had done something wrong, or maybe I needed to report a bug, but I couldn't find any place to do either thing, either in the app or on the Be My Eyes website. Hopefully whoever called was answered by someone else and not just left hanging? (Still 4 stars because I'm not the one it needs to work for, I'm just a volunteer.)

I just received my first call! I helped an older lady with matching her shirt to her shoes. Something so simple, but it made my heart so full. Like...its hard to explain but just being able to assist someone who needs your help with something you take for granted everyday, being able to see. I will always have this app downloaded! Definitely recommend! It is a very rewarding experience/feeling!â¤

Love the concept! This app is doing a wonderful service to people in need. I wish I could write a personal review, but after almost a year I've never gotten to use it. Not a bad thing. There just aren't as many needing help as there are volunteers. I'm uninstalling only because I actually forgot I still had this app, and I don't want to get caught off guard if a call ever does come in from it.

I love the concept a lot but I have a problem I got two calls on March 8th the day I signed up but I haven't gotten a call since currently It's July 22 and I don't think this is even fixable but it was the only reason I'm giving it four stars Update: I got a call today! I was able to help someone find clorox wipes. I'm so glad this app exists.

5-star concept 1-star app execution Such a great concept but the app sucks. Calls won't connect video, so you have to take manual screenshots every few seconds to try to keep up. Additionally, all "send feedback" options instead trigger "share" actions, so no way in-app to submit feedback. I tried via [settings > share feedback] as well as [stories > share your story > contact us]. This review is specific to the latest Android app on Google Pixel 4XL.

It's interesting, but if you don't answer within the first few seconds someone else get it. It's like they send a call to everyone in the app at the same time to answer. Had a guy call me that I'm unsure was visually impaired though, seems like he just wanted to talk to me about my personal relationship with Jesus Christ. Did not appreciate being hijacked by a witness when trying to help people. Other than that it's been cool!

Love the idea of the app but since you have so many visual volunteers perhaps we can list special skills. For example I'm a Registered Nurse, I would be happy to help explain medication or prescription instructions, our guide someone through doing a bandage change even if a sighted person is present.

Much like what Bart Ouwerkerk said 5 days ago in his Jan.25,'21 review, I absolutely LOVED the idea of this app. My maternal grandmother was at the forefront of Braille translation, doing thousands of papers & books into Braille for many decades until she passed in 1974, & this app/idea felt like a tiny connection to her - a simple, fine way to assist the visually challenged. So I installed the app about 2-1/2 years ago. And then?...Zero. Zippo. Zilch! Not *one single call* in well over a year. Living where I do in N.E. of U.S. - a highly populated area of the world & just 25 miles from Manhattan - you'd think there'd be SOMEONE around (w/in 50 mile radius at least, w/so many cities nearby, much less globally!) that needed help at some point, but nope, not a one! Makes me wonder how that's logistically even possible. So I finally deleted it. Somehow, somewhere, something's not right. A real shame, I would've loved to help. Hopefully some are anyway.

I haven't used it yet but I will and I think this is fantastic. I read a few reviews about people not recieving calls for months. I'm leaving this review to see how far you guys have gone on advertising this app directly to the ones who actually need it. Hospitals, retirement homes, homes for the blind should be places to target to expand the audience and customer's in need or people who want to help. A lot of people can get it for their love ones. Keep up the good work though.

I had the most amazing experience today. The app connects visually impaired users with people who can help with using internet, reading signs, identifying objects, etc. Someone from India called. I helped them fill out CAPTCHA to view results of a job screening exam. I read out their scores too. So cool! I was called to help because I speak Marathi.

I love this app! My husband and I answered our first call a couple months ago. We both helped a young lady out from California. With everything being so negative these days it was really nice to be able to connect with someone across the country and help them out when they needed it and I really did feel like we made a difference that day thank you for this opportunity.

wonderful idea! can you make another version of this app called "be my ears"? I, personally, have had hearing issues for a long time and think this would help people who are hearing impaired as much as it has helped people who are visually impaired. Keep up the good work!

I recieved my very first call about a month ago and it was for an elderly lady that wanted to make sure her outfit matched!! I love to be able to help... I wish I got more calls though... I have had this app about a year and only been used that once... still an A+++++ app and idea!!! Maybe you can come up with ansign language interpreter!!!

The idea of the app is amazing! I'm Excited to be apart of it. However, I got my first call tonight but it wouldn't answer. It kept saying trying to connect and I felt as though I let whoever was on the other side down. I then tried to open the app but it just kept loading. Bummer. Hopefully next time it'll work.

Received my first call within days of signin up. But it was a man in another country just trying to flash the call recipient. The call ended abruptly after he appeared on camera pantsless and the option to leave feedback that pops up after the call didn't actually function. Like it was just for show. Obviously people can just sign up and abuse this app and I'm concerned there's no protection against this. Just "call recipient beware".

I am a sighted person and was so excited to receive my first call today! The audio was clear and torch (flashlight) controls worked wonderfully. However the video would frequently freeze making it difficult for me to aid the caller. Overall brilliant concept and great app

I downloaded this app a year ago and have been lucky enough to have been able to help several people on here. They'll call you through the app, so nobody has your personal info, which is great! It's quick & easy to setup & you can help immediately! You can help whenever someone calls you & if you're busy you can let it go & they'll get connected to someone else because they have over a million volunteers! A great way to give back & help others, ESPECIALLY now with the craziness going on!q

I have been a volunteer for a year. I have received 3 calls total. 2 while I was at work anf unable to answer. The 3rd I answered, but the video did not work, the audio was breaking up and then we were disconnected. It is an amazing idea and I'm sure helps a lot of people, but I think they have more volunteers than are needed. After a year I am considering uninstalling to free up the space on my phone.

I got my first call today but missed it because my phone (almost always kept on vibrate) didn't vibrate. I just happened to look at the screen at the last second. Does your ringer have to be on, or do you have to be staring at your screen when a call comes in? I would love an option to allow vibrate notifications so I have a better chance of responding to a call.

so I've had this app on my phone for about 3 years and I have NEVER received a call. I'm one of those horrible people that always has my phone in my hand so I figured this is great. Except that whatever algorithm this app uses doesn't work right. My coworker downloaded the app and got over 10 calls in less than 4 months. I love the concept but you need to fix the call distribution system.
replyContent: Hello Alyssa, we apologise for your experience. Your coworker seems lucky, and must be rated positively by the users, because it might take some time to get calls among 3+ million volunteers. Thank you for the feedback!

content: installed this app in July last year...tonight I got my first call! super user friendly and it's silly but to finally get a call and help someone was super rewarding. took 3 minutes or so out of my night. wish I could help more but i love that this service is there for the blind and visually impaired

I've only answered one call. It was very simple. A package to the wrong house, they wanted help reading the name. Took less than 5 minutes. The visual quality of the video was disappointing. Since that's the most important part, it was not easy to read lines of text coming through but we got it done. Better video quality is a must.

Great concept but there needs to be a way of setting available hours. Also it might be nice to have a way to set things like "override my hours if the caller is declaring an emergency" (call urgency). Keep working on it.

As volunteers who want to help and users who need help, people should be sharing this app like gossip at a church picnic. With so many volunteers, just about every informational resource available to visually impaired people should include this app. The ratio of volunteers/users is so immense, getting an actual call to action once a year is understandable. I'm going to be in a bit of self denial about the Data-Mining reviews, I'm hoping the trackers are to enhance connectivity.

Great asset for visually impaired people! (From what I've heard; I'm a volunteer). Very simple and easy to understand and use for a sighted person/volunteer! (I can't say how it is being blind on the app versus being a volunteer, but the community stories that I've read are really positive).

An amazing app that lets sighted people help visually impaired people do the things we take for granted. I've only received one call but it was a great feeling to be able to help her get the right frozen meal out of the freezer area. Do it! Get the app!

such a great app. im a colorblind makeup artist and sometimes I need help telling deep colors apart. when I call theres always someone there to help me sort it out. I dont have to look inept and ask people on set. its awesome.

Great app idea! I got a call but I couldn't hear him. He could hear me so I read him all I could see then said maybe he would like to call back for a clearer connection I wasn't sure but I did all I could with what I had. I've been helping blind people all my life as one of the greatest women in my life was blind, my grandmother. Sad I couldn't fully help because of a connection problem.

This app is a great concept however when I first started using it I could get videos from ppl I was helping. Now all I get is still shot pics. It makes it a little more difficult to help out. I wish you all would fix this asap!!

I just answered my first call and it was amazing! This app is very easy to use and when a call came through, it connected quick with decent resolution. This app really does help with the little things that those with vision take advantage of.

Great idea but never worked for me. Tried the test call, got the video but no sound. Tried to use the contact support function but it just opened a share link. Have had the app installed for about a year but never gotten a call to help someone... I hope it's working better for it's intended recipients.

Need to be able to add availability for those answering calls. I had the app closed and still received a call while working. I feel so terrible having to decline the call when someone needs help but unfortunately I can't answer the phone when working as I work in a call center

Got my first call today! Was a very good experience, someone needed help reading labels. Only reason not 5 stars is because the video lagged badly, which made it take more time to read for the person. Had a good connection with audio, and was connected via wifi, so not sure what the vid issue was

I want to give this app 5 stars. But the first call I was able to answer, the person needed my help reading a document in a language I didn't know! I felt awful because I wanted to help and couldn't. I thought my settings were set up for English, and when I went to double check, it just sits on a "Please wait..." Screen. Please continue to refine this app to make sure we can help more folks.

I LOVE the concept of this app. However, the last two times I got a call and went to answer it froze. Please fix it. I really love the app and want to be able to answer the calls. The first time worked perfectly, but not the last two.

Finally got a call today that I was able to accept in time. I could hear and see the person in need of help perfectly, but unfortunately they could not hear me. Not sure if it was an issue with my device, their device or the app itself, however I was a bit disappointed.

I just got my first call and it was amazing to help someone out. The gentleman who called needed help for their fashion class in college and had me look up a dance video to describe their clothing. This helped him get through his big project and felt great!!! This app is amazing!!!

I think that the app is a great concept, when it works. I've only been able to answer one call and the call was super grainy. I could not help like I needed to. I had a call that I could not answer at all. The app froze as I was trying to send feedback on a recent call and when it finally started up again it chose the call experience was good and it was not. If the bugs can be fixed, it'd be a great app!!

Answered twice, both didn't work. The thought behind the app is wonderful. I really wanted to help. In total, I recieved two calls. Both times, the quality of the videos were so terrible that I couldn't read the information they needed. I'm not sure if it's the app, my end, or theirs. The frustration, however, has lead me to no longer participate.

I'm giving only four stars because it's a very good concept but it takes a little while for anyone to get a call and help someone so they think that this app is just going to be a waste of space so maybe you could try to get on local news to see if anyone that doesn't know about this app specially blind people know about it so we can get more calls and like people can feel better about themselves

I hope someone's sees this I've been using the app for a little while and only had 1 call so far but the call I had did have some issues with connecting our cameras it just stayed loading and when I tried to send feedback through the app It uses the send feedback option as a share button like I'm trying to send the feedback to and app or other or contacts on my phone. I have a Galaxy Note 10.

Thank you for adding still image option - I did not use it this time as gentleman did not ask for much detail. If he needed more information, this feature would have been especially helpful. I sincerely appreciate the opportunities to be of service - such a beautiful thing!

I've had this app for many months and just got my first phone call today. I helped a lady identify dollar denominations. It feels good to be able to assist people. It's too bad I don't get the opportunity to assist more often, but looking at the number of volunteers compared to the number of blind users it makes sense.

It's a great idea, I haven't answered a call yet, but the only reason I gave 4 stars is because apparently the app has to be open to get calls, at least that's how I saw it works on my phone. I left the app open and I got my first call in the morning (I didn't receive any since I downloaded the app) and while I was at he dentist I couldn't answer at the time. So my guess is that it only works if it's open, would be great if you could fix it.

I personally relate to the mission of this app and seeing so many people lend their time in search of helping the visually impaired is heart warming and if you're even thinking of downloading this app to help even just in your spare time, please do. It makes a world of difference.

Amazing app for both the fully able and those in need of assistance. My first call was more than just helping. Had a wonderful conversation with a stranger on the other side of the world to find out they were raised in the same city as me. Small world!

Love the idea.. if it only worked... finally got my first call and it said "establishing network..." forever.. had the app for months and finally got my first call but couldn't help.. the poor guy just wanted to know what setting his washer was on. I felt so bad I couldn't help.

this is a brilliant idea for an app! I think it is important that it is simple and straightforward so there is no confusions in the main objective is solely for helping somebody else, as opposed to apps that would bribe you with reward. excellent job on this app

Great resource. There are so many more volunteers that people who actually need help. Which is fantastic, however, the app is taking space and I've never used it in the month I've had it so I may end up deleting it if I'm not needed. Keep in mind that this just means that they are already receiving help from someone else, which is GREAT. ðŸ’• So happy that there is a resource like this for the blind. ðŸ˜Š

I've had the app for months. Someone else would always answer a call before I could answer, but I finally accepted my first call today. Made the wait well worth it. Felt great to help someone. Don't get discouraged if you feel like you'll never get a call, when you finally get one, you'll be so excited ðŸ˜Š

This is such an amazing app, I'm just a volunteer but I think this is such an amazing and creative idea!! And it's super convenient that others are notified too so that I dont feel bad if I cant answer right away haha!

Great initiative but app is not. I never get video connected so it doesn't serve the purpose. I had to ask callers twice that they need to call again as I have connectivity issues. Feedback button also does not work so I'm providing my feedback here.
the idea is really exceptional but my first call after 2 weeks of having the app was just a guy showing his private parts!
Just had my first call to help a gentleman. He needed help picking out the colors for his clothes. Awesom app. Clear video and audio. Great experience. Thank you for putting this app together.

To the people giving 1 star for never receiving a call... You realize there are ~140,000 blind people using the app and over 2.3 million volunteers? That means you have a 1 in 16 chance of getting a call every time there's a call. No reason to give low ratings.

Has to be one of the most genius ideas put into a very well functioning app. Got my first call from a blind participant and everything went smoothly as it could have and it's nice to know you've helped someone with their day.
What an awesome app! I just took my first call and helped a woman shut off her stove. Such a simple act. I feel good about this! And the app worked seamlessly.

Haven't got my first call yet but this app gets the best rating from me absolutely possible just on idea. I'm sure the service is great aswell but I cant honestly say yet. We need more people like the creators of this app and more apps the bring love to the world. Thank you so much to whomever had a hand in putting this app on the market. You all truly are heroes!!
Awesome app. Awards should be given to the creator. I 100% recommend it and wish that more visually disabled people were aware that it was available as a resource to them. â­â­â­â­â­

I just downloaded this app and I'm so so exited to start helping out. I am bilingual and happy to help in both English and Spanish languages, however, the app only allows me to choose one language. If there's a way to select more than 1 language would be great.

I'm a sighted user of this app and I believe this could be a fantastic tool for anyone with a sight disability. It gives me a little hope for humanity that there are about 10 sighted users for every 1 blind user and that the sighted users are doing this for free.

Awesome app for helping people the issue is its rare that you get calls which is both good and sucks. I wish you could toggle something to be ready to receive calls because there's been 2 cases where I've gotten calls at bad times.

Its a great idea I just wish there was a way we could specify what times we are unable to answer calls! I'm usually working Monday thru Wednesday and the weekend so cant always answer calls before 5:30pm!

Great concept but app needs work. I received a call for help today but the video was black and I only could occasionally get a still image to load. It was very frustrating for the caller who needed help
Very cool idea, poor execution I've had this app for like TWO YEARS, just got my first call, and it wouldn't answer. Hit the "Answer" button at least 50 times, and nothing, until it stopped ringing.

Without my glasses, I'm considered blind. I've looked for my glasses when I couldn't find them for up to a week. A volunteer helped me find them one of the times... I had to go somewhere I just hope I never loose my glasses and my phone at the same time

The app works really well and is a good way to help people. I've only ever gotten one call but that's very understandable as according to the count in the app there are 3 million volunteers and only around two hundred thousand blind people using it so it makes sense that calls would be rare
It is an amazing concept and a useful tool. There are literally millions of volunteers, so getting calls are rare, but it is extremely useful for the blind. I love being able to help someone

Great idea but just collecting dust. I had the app about a month without getting any notifications or calls I love the idea of this but maybe there is a app issue or more than enough have signed up and it over crowded with people who want to help but that's not a bad thing if that's the casr

this is an incredible app and the people behind it are wonderful human beings. the only reason that it is 4 stars and not 5 is because you cant set times of availability. if this is fixed i will rate 5 stars
I wish I could change the ringtone so I knew what the heck was going on as soon as someone was trying to reach me. I tried to provide this feedback in the app, but the feedback button doesn't work.

Should a stop and start time option. And a flagging option as well, like every other service you will spammer, scammers and just bad people. Upon fixing that you will get 5stars.. great idea! Congrats!
I feel so helpful, can't believe I received the second phone call and was able to help, .its a great app. Hope to see more apps like this one, thanks to the founder of it

This is the most amazing app I have ever come across. The ability to help another person in need weather near or far, small need or large. Whoever created this is a true hero. My only wish is to help whenever I can. Thank you and God bless.

I hope more apps like this would be cretaed to help people who have disadvantages in life! Besides, ony forst call, i met a person who needs help on a medicine's direction. As the image is a bit blurry ( i dont know if it was because my wifi or because of the app) i cant see the direction and decided to go to google to find that brand. As i head to google, i cant get back to the call and he cant hear me so he has to ended the call. I feel so sad and guilty. I'm so sorry Mr. Stranger :(

Having issues with connecting with the person in need. I answer the call and then it says forever trying to answer call with no success. Have had this happen several times.

I love this idea and have been contacted several times, for help. However, there were two times where I have been disconnected by the other user, by mistake. Then I couldn't finish helping him /her. Is there a way to communicate with the person you help, if you get disconnected by accident?
For some reason the last 2-3 calls just spin and say connecting and it never connects.

Had a call once that i couldn't even answer, other than that it was just spam notifications of "inspirational stories" from the developers. then suddenly it wasn't installed anymore. Great idea. have no idea if it actually helps anyone.
replyContent: Hello Chris, thank you for your nice words! Since we have 3+ million volunteers, it might take time to get a call. All we can ask for is your patience, we hope you will catch a call quite soon. In the meantime you can help spread the word about Be My Eyes in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users.

content: Amazing idea, and super easy to use. The only downside is that because there are so many volunteers, it might be a while before you get your first call. But answering calls and helping is simple and people are very appreciative.
I love the idea and all that but when I try and answer it won't sometimes and the camera doesn't work when it does answer

Amazing. Just got my first call today. Takes a while to get one but it's worth it. The only reason it takes so long is because they have so many volunteers. The creators of the app have done a wonderful job.
This is what a global network like the Internet should be used for more than it has been in the past. What a great idea: crowd-sourcing immediate sighted assistance for the visually impaired!

per some old reviews I read regarding muting the app notifications only, not your whole phone: the app now has a setting to make notifications vibrate / ring & more. You can even customize the notification souns
This app is awesome! I can honestly say this app is extremely helpful and the live assistants are quick, friendly and knowledgeable. This app has helped my daily life struggles!

Awesome and such a great way to help... This is such an easy way for you to help your fellow people that need assistance with day to day things. The payback in knowing you were able to help someone by doing something because you have sight and they don't shows how we take things for granted some time. Do us all a favor and help out and volunteer ðŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ ðŸ™ ðŸ˜‰

I have been a volunteer since 2018 and am so grateful for the opportunity to be of service and meet people from all over the world. The app is really easy to use. Video quality suffers when working off of cell data but if on wifi, great to go. Please volunteer especially if you speak unique languages.
Such an awesome way to give back! It takes such little effort to help somebody and makes so much difference. EVERYONE should be able to take 5 minutes out of their time to answer a call. ðŸ’œ

Great idea, but I told my blind friends about it and it turns out they would have to pay to access the app. I have an Android and I'm guessing they are using iPhones. The blind should be exempt from the fee. I don't want to use it if they are not.
replyContent: Hi Kai, our app is completely free both on Android and iOS, for both volunteers and blind/low vision users no matter how much they use it.

content: I've helped assist people in choosing clothing color, monetary value, pick up pet poop, and learn stovetop knobs. Be thankful that you can use your eyes! I'm glad mine can be used by others when needed.
It was an awesome experience! I had a little trouble with the focus trying to see the date on a bottle, but then we adjusted on his end and I was able help. it really felt good!
I love this app, the thought of helping someone is so satisfying. A women called needing help picking out a flavor coffee and helping her with her mail. I enjoy being a volunteer.
I love this app. Although I've only ever received one phone call. Wish I could be of more help but good to know there is more than enough help out there for the visually impaired who use this app.

You will never regret using this app to help someone! It is the most amazing feeling to be able to see for someone who has impaired vision. Volunteer to help someone else today - it will help you, too!

My very first call a woman had lost her meds they fell beside the couch. With her ordinarily ordered arrangement now in a disarray she wasn't sure which meds were which. It seems like such a simple thing, the blessing of sight. And to be able to share it with someone and know that they are living independently and safer gave me the strongest feeling of community belonging I think I ever felt. She helped me. God gave us all something to give. What you choose to do is up to you.

I have finished my first call successfully, by helping someone sort products and reading the labels for them. This app is very rewarding opportunity to volunteer my vision in service of those who may have the need.
This is the most amazing concept! It's so nice that we can all help another person with simple, everyday things. Reading a label, find something they can't and just be someone to aid.
I helped my first person it was great! I wish, there was a way to set the app to only vibrate when I get a call though because I woke up from sleeping to answer it.

I remember being ten and wanting to make an app like this. But I never made it. I'm glad someone else did. I'm so excited to help someone!!! Wonderful idea and thank you for doing this for visually impaired people
easy to use - ive had two calls since June when i volunteered. both were under 5 minutes, and it is a great joy to be able to help those that need something simple i can do from anywhere.

I haven't quite gotten used to the app, but when I got my first call, it was amazing, I helped someone grab strawberry yogurt, and the nice lady on the other end said thank you so many times it made me so super happy.
Pretty good app for blind people eventhough the odds of being called to help a blind person is next to zero since there are more registered volunteers than actual blinds. Still a noble app.

This app is one of the few things on the internet, I'd go as far as to say in the world if technology, that consistently gives me joy from fulfilling a sense of purpose, but that being said I wish there were less volunteers so that I could answer more calls.

So I downloaded this app Yesterday, and I just got my first call! Not only is this app helping people who are blind or have bad vision, but it also makes people who help them feel like better people! It's a win-win in my book.

Heartwarming! I received my 1st call the day after I added the app. Nervously, I answered the call and was able to help a kind gentleman set his thermostat. Though it was a simple task, it made me realize how blessed I am and how I can be a blessing to others. Keep the calls comingðŸ˜Š
The idea seems very promising, but there's not much to the app. I think there should at least be more options so that you can set a certain time of day or something that you're available.
i absolutely love this app! i heard about it from my friend and i had to do this. im 13 years old and I've gotten at least 10 calls so far. this app is absolutely amazing

I'm extremely grateful for this service. As my eyes continue to get worse I continue to get more apprehensive. Thanks to this app some of that has subsided. Knowing help is just a phone call away provides a comfort I needed.

So i got this app a few days ago and i got my First Call but once i answered it logged me off and said there was an error. :( theres nothing to do with my connection. I love the app but i hope this wont happen again.
Outstanding app, but currently has 17 volunteers for each visually impaired user, so you don't get many calls at all.
This is an awesome application. I received my first call several days ago and helped a guy input information into his device. Love it!

I just completed my first volunteer call, I've never done so little and felt so good about it. I just want to thank the creators of this app for making something like this, it makes me feel better about the future of my one year old son who's blind. I would give it a ten billion star rating if I could.

I never get calls. I've had this app for months and haven't had a single call. I feel like it's useless for me to have this app if I never get the chance to help. Note: I have limited storage on my phone and I often have to uninstall apps I haven't used if I want to install another app.
This app is something amazing. I got my first call today and I'm so glad I got to pick up. I made someone's day and it made me feel better about mine. 10/10 definitely recommend.
It was incredible to be able to use something i take for granted every day to help someone in need. MY EYES! Simple and free. I highly recommend this app!

im beyond amazed! got my 1st call in 24hrs of downloading. helped a woman pick eye shadow. its easy and very helpful to peoplr who are blind or close to. youll feel so happy n proud. just do it and help!
So far, I'm unable to use this. I went to make the test call and there was absolutely no sound, and then all apps in my phone stopped making sound too. Some kind of bug.

So i joined up cause i wanted to help and this was a neat idea... my very first call, it was some guy masterbating in what looked like a child's room...i clicked off it so fast that the end call/ rate the experience button i clicked off trying to get out of the call and the app has no contact info/ customer service to really report the phone call after the inital end screen. A lot of people are going to end up abusing this service which is a shame.
replyContent:
Hi Stephanie, 

we are extremely sorry that you have experienced inappropriate behaviour in the Be My Eyes app! We do not tolerate abuse. At the end of every call, you have the possibility to report an abuse directly to us. We then proceed to block the reported user forever. 

You can also contact us at info@bemyeyes.com

content: On my first call I helped someone make sure that their oven was preset to the correct temperature. I think this is a very rewarding app to install on your phone.
Haven't had my first call yet, so I cannot give feedback regarding the matching process. I wish there was a function to set times for when we are available and not.
I've had 3 calls total, one I had a conversation where I was able to help someone until the audio stopped working. The other two have me an error message when I answered
I've only had one call but it absolutely made my day to speak to Ashley and assist her... This app is above and beyond amazing and I can't wait for my next call! ðŸ˜

I just helped a woman identify the box she had in her hands. The entire process was simple, friendly, and humbling. The app worked perfectly. Seamless.
Whenever i get a call from someone the screen stays black and i can't see what is the person want to show me, and it feels bad not to be able to help after i get the call
By far the easiest and simplest way to volunteer to help someone, but at the same time make a big impact for those who need it. I honestly look forward to answering requests on this. Fantastic app.

I have helped some people and can't answer some phone calls. It is frustrating as I try to swipe with no answer as my app will not respond. Frustrating!!!

Have only been lucky enough to receive one call so far, but wow, talk about humbling! I helped a sweet woman match an outfit. I realized real quick how much I take for granted. Beautiful app!
(I'm a sighted person) I've only gotten a few calls so far and each time I've tried to answer them, I've gotten an error message and the call drops. Anyone else had this issue?

Wonderful concept and it is executed very well. I've had a couple different calls in the months I've had the app Ave it seems to be a great resource.
absolutely amazing app! I'll be blind one day when im much older so its very rewarding to be able to help other blind people while i can see

I feel like everyone needs to download this app, it made me feel so good to complete my first call that now i anticipate new calls. This is... It's just beautiful.

Definitely a very helpful tool. It took a while to get a call but if finally helped someone and it was very rewarding! ðŸ¥°

You rarely get called, but that's a good thing. I've had the app for almost 4 years and I've only gotten a chance to help 2 people. This app is a great way to do something small to help someone in need.
such an amazing idea, and wonderful execution by the dev team! simple, but powerful. haven't had a crash or bug to report thus far!
This app is amazing I'm glad I get to help the vision impaired I answered my first call an helped a lady out I felt really good to know I helped her with her clothing

So far I have only received 1 call but it made my day to be able to help someone! And answering the call was super easy! Great app and idea!
I finally received a call but it never connected. I ended the call and hope that the person needing assistance didn't think I hung up on them. Maybe look into connection issues.

content: This concept is really good and its always good to help someone who's in need.
It is great for blind low vision. My son has rs1 so it's important to me
Completely simple, straight, and quite easy to use.
How about adding an option to get more calls if someone wants to?
Have attempted to take three calls and none of them connect please fix

Not sure why but I have received only one call and it was prankster pretending to be blind. They started swearing and verbally abusing me while I was with my children. No way to report them either. Disappointed that people are using this as a joke and taking away from people who actually need help. I'll keep the app for now but the next time it happens I'm removing it. There should be a way to report these jerks.
It's totally fine the stories are mice however if there is a week Wi-Fi connection from the client that needs the volunteer it does become which can make their volunteer feel inadequate
This is an amazing app. I truly enjoy helping someone every time I get a call.
Can't answer calls. Just says "Trying to answer call" forever.
I downloaded the app a few months ago, couldn't take the first call i got immediately so i missed that. Today, I finally got to help someone identify currencies. I feel so good about that.
App doesn't work. I press answer it it just says trying to answer for over a minute.
Got my first call today and it would not let me accept the call after 10 times trying to accept but it did let me decline ... Needs to be fixed asap how can I help when I can answer. 11/13/21
This morning I helped a person identify and change settings on their heater. I always feel good when I can help another person! -Cara Kaiser
Whenever I receive a call and I try to answer it never goes through.

Im so happy to help blind people.

One time, a male asked me whether his trimmed beard is good or whether it requires further trimming. He doesn't seems to be a blind person. I was unable to process that if it's appropriate to ask so . I replied "yes" and then called off. After the call, I wasn't able to "report the issue" which is a option given to choose after a call.
Joined yesterday and just got my first call!! This is such a great idea and I am so happy to be a part of itâ¤
I'm more than glad to help visually impaired people through this app. Thanks
This is good app. Volunteer job are available for manðŸŒ·ðŸŒ·
Amazing! Just helped someone with cooking instructions.
Amazing. Helping people with no gain feels good and we should all do it more often

content: I love the idea of the app i hope i receive my first call very soon

Amazing app to help people.
What a brilliant idea! Cant wait to use it or to be of help to others. Thank you for creating a way to give help freely and easily....
With so many volunteers I want sure if I would get any calls but I have had 2 so far. Call quality has been great both times
It's really work, i've just recived a call and i helped him. Wonderful app for everyone. Much obligated to you guys

Great app, great idea!!!!
A great platform for those wanna help people. It will give u a piece of heaven.
Just completed my first call. Everything worked fine, and being able to help people is great.
The idea is excellent but why every call come to me when I was sleeping?! It will be better to improve the app with the option of selection the best time for you to receive calls.
IMPOSSIBLE TO PICK UP! AMAZING IDEA, NON-EXISTENT EXECUTION.
