content: This app helps pepole that are blind good work pepole
The felling of helping someone of the comfort of my house or office is so satisfying
This is really a good concept. Glad to help others through this app
The single most wholesome app I've ever encountered

Could not connect to a single call although my internet connection is stable and other apps are working well as usual. Could not provide feedback in the app itself either. The screen froze every time I clicked on the Feedback button. Overall, a great initiative and I wish I was able to connect to callers and help out the community.
Its great being able to help people.
I've only been called to help a few times but it's a good experience.

Wonderful idea but for some technical glitch when I get a call it never rings so I don't understand when I get a call. Only when I open the app I get to hear a ringtone. It's not possible to always keep the App Page open. Also, sometimes even if it rang twice & I received the call it shows it's been attended by someone else. Please sort it out
I never rate any app. But this is how execellent idea. I have to say nothing anything wrong good luck buddies
I felt great being helpful. Very easy.

I received my first call today. It was so cool that I could help someone. One thing that would he cool is of there was a a log in your profile that tells you how many people you helped and where they are from. Would be super neat.

I love this app! Ive only had 5 or 6 successful calls in 2 years but with 5mil volunteers thats to be expected. The reason i give 4 instead of 5 stars is because ive received 1 or 2 calls that wouldn't connect for some reason and therefore i couldnt help those people. Other than that i love this app and think its a fantastic way of helping out the blind community- being able to make a small difference to someone's day is nice :)
Great app. Simple to use for both sighted and not. Feels good to help.
Excellent concept brought to fruition.
I love this so much ðŸ¥° I am apparently at my best when I'm helping others so this is perfect. Great job creators.

Love it, but app is buggy. I've gotten 4 calls so far, and was only able to help with the first one. The remaining calls were not able to be opened because the app isn't working. Please fix it soon, I'd love to keep contributing!

So far received 4 calls but managed to help out 2 due to unfamiliar with the ring tone. Recent help was able to use the flash light tools to light up the environment and see clearly the surrounding. Just hope the flash light will turn off after the call ends, if not, it sure will drain the phone battery.
The mission is beautiful, the sole proprietor is a fraud ðŸ˜›

Neat experience getting to give assistance to someone in this unique way. Both my calls have been very pleasant. Video quality could have been better, then again I have spotty internet service sometimes, as could the other person. Only downside is you may wait months between calls, but regardless I look forward to them!
The best app I have on my phone, hands down. Glad someone took the initiative.
It keeps crashing
Great initiative....but my app keeps hanging after every caller I call/attend and then I have reinstall to keep it running.... please resolve.

Getting a call is really satisfying, but with the one I have had so far the video never started. I was able to use the snapshot tool to get around that but the video was black with a "connecting call" message spinning on top.

Hi! I would really love for the app to have a report button of some sort. I just got a call of help from the app unfortunately the person calling us showing his private part to me. I feel like such person should not be allowed to continue to be in that app as for no other people to fall his victim. Hopefully you can consider this idea.

Stop giving one star or so cause 'there's not enough blind people'. Like, uhm, what? Isn't not being fast enough to be the first one to accept a call a good sign? The app is working just fine and supporting the blind well. I can understand y'all do want to help, but they know best when and how often they need help, don't push them into 'needing' help!

A brilliant, simple idea, tech at its most useful. I'm totally blind with friends and family but even so I feel an increased sense of independence with the app. It is potentially even more useful for a blind person on their own. I've had help to sort food packages, tins, get my tele started. I'm constantly pushing my sighted friends to sign and I'm winning. For any potential volunteer, you can't overestimate the importance of the time you are giving, a minute from you and you can free a log jam.

feedback: had my first call and it was really exciting! 2 improvements. 1) when the call comes in, it should indicate the language you should speak in. i have mine set as multilingual, and the individual who called did not speak my default language in English. awkward at first. 2) how can you set the phone call to silent if youre in a meeting? i would like to mute it but not my entire phone.

I REALLY love the idea of helping blind or low sighted people all over the world with just a call. Right now its over 2 million volunteers and about 100 thousand low sighted/blind people that could call you and it only takes about 1-5 minutes helping them out. Mostly you get asked simple questions like what color a shirt has for example. It always makes me feel happier after helping a person and maybe even making their day a little better. (Everyone I met so far was really sweet and polite.)
Good idea but I answered my first call today and the app wouldn't show me the video just the loading symbol and "trying to connect call". Why is it doing that and how do I fix it?
Such a wonderful idea! I've only been able to answer one call so far since they seem to be picked up really fast! But the video quality can be improved slightly. Other than that, a great initiative.

The idea is amazing. However changes need to be made so it doesn't become just another forgotten app. I have been a member for over a month and nothing, so either blind people aren't using it or the filter are not well planned out. There should be a way of putting more than one language which would help increasing chances of getting calls for those who speak more than one language. I strongly believe in the whole idea for this app but changes and maybe a better publicity for it in the blind community should be made so that it can truly bring a great experience to all it's users

The app is a great idea, but lacks essential features. There is no available/busy status. Can only go offline by logging out. It is pointless to contact someone who's unavailable. I recommend a 3 status system. On call ( prioritize to me), available (regular priority), busy (no call requests). I recommend creating PC version, perhaps a web portal. Computer screens are better for video and better assitance could be provided. Perhaps have an volunteer operator style setup option.
i got a call it was awesome experience i felt much better afterwards this made me of help to others and the experience is priceless

Great app, loved the idea. One suggestion if I may; add an ON/OFF option at the app's home screen where I can activate receiving a help request, as I might be in a meeting, asleep or even low on GSM data where I can't accept calls, by this everyone can activate the app whenever they are ready to lend a hand and by this saving time for the requesting part not to wait longer for the app directing the call to others if the first didn't answer.

What an absolutely amazing idea for an app. Have already made many of my friends and family download this app. And the fact that you rarely get a call (which many people seem to be complaining about) is actually a good thing. It means there are enough volunteers that no one seems burdened by having to take frequent calls, so I urge people not to delete it just because you haven't got a call.

i really love the idea behind this app! i've just downloaded it and one of the first questions was wich of the two i am, a volunteer or a visually impaired person.. i think it would be nice to choose both. i have terrible eyesight without my glasses(-10 and distortion) so if i don't know where my glasses are, i'm screwed. would be nice if i was able to volunteer but also receive help if needed.

As a volunteer I love this app. I have some disabilities that are not sight related so know what's it's like to be limited sometimes. Being unable to work this app helps me 'give back' a little. It's nice to be the one helping someone else for a change and I don't even need to be able to get out of bed. It means no matter how unwell I feel I can do something good :) So far the app has run smoothly - it's functional.
The interface of application didn't show the call. It has only sound so the users have to go the app icon and answer the call, to late to help them.

Downloaded the app a year ago. I had previously had two or three failed call attempts (one or two too slow or busy, and another with either connection or user issues). Today I finally had another call and it was successful. It certainly helps to know several languages and indicate it on your profile, that way you're open to more people. And another review mentioned the app needed to be open to receive calls but that's not the case, unless that was changed in an update at some point. Excellent.

Hi guys, I love the idea behind this app, but I have 2 things to add as feedback, hope this helps you: i) I've never been able to answer a single call, as it disconnects as soon as it rings, and; ii) lately the app is constantly popping up whilst I'm in the middle of using other apps, typing messages on WhatsApp, using Spotify, etc. It's really rather annoying, and it keeps re-opening even after I've shut it. Thanks for all the hard work though, good luck! :)

This is a wonderful idea. I'll never remove this app. The only suggestion I have is it would be good to be able to set active hours as a sighted person. I have to turn notifications off when i go to bed, but may not remember to turn them back on when i get up. If you could set active hours it would be perfect. Also my phone is on silent 95% of the time. I'd love to be able to set this app to still ring even when on silent. Otherwise this is an outstanding app, I'll be recommending to everyone

I downloaded this app with the intent to help blind people and the visually impaired. when reading through the terms of use, I found out that they will have the right to use and monetize anyting you create on this app including whatever is said and recorded over video. I do not like videos of me being used and monitored without my consent, so I ended up deleting the app. Please add a choice to not grant access to the content, as I really want to help the impaired.
replyContent: Hello, we need to record videos for safety and security concerns. Yet, a very selected number of people from our team have access to those videos. No video will ever be used or be published for any reason and on any platform without your consent.

content: I love the idea. And to be honest, I first learned about Be My Eyes from a blind friend which led me to download the app. I have gotten one call so far. But just now I realized that probably the team can make an option for vibration as notification when someone is calling or even sound when my phone is set to silent mode. Bcs that's what I do to my phone most of the time. Although it does not mean I wouldn't answer if there is a call. I hope my suggestion is understood. Thank you!

I saw this app while browsing the Google play store a few days ago and thought the concept was quite interesting. I set up a profile as a sighted volunteer (which took under 2 mins to do) and didn't really think much more of it not expecting much really, but tonight I got a call through from a lovely man looking for help to search through a stack of CDs to find the one he wanted to listen to. This app is an amazingly simple and easy way to make everyday living easier for visually impaired people

The app seems to be focusing too much on collecting the volunteers email and getting permission to send spam. You can't start anything without giving a real email (already a red flag). And the home screen is designed to eventually get your consent to send spam. There is no simple opt out. That doesn't seem like the purpose of the app is helping blind people. It's collecting your data.

I'm a volunteer on this app and I absolutely adore it. I get a couple of calls a month perhaps from blind people who need help with various daily tasks, such as identifying "use by"-dates on packaging and we always end up having a lovely chat. It's really made me realise how little the world caters to blind people, so I'm now also supporting a charity that trains guide dogs. Highly recommend this app!

Great app. let's us contribute in making the world little more accessible for the visually impaired. A great tool to increase the bonding between those who can see the world with their eyes and those who can not. A great way to bridge the divide and help create a collaborative world. Hope, people come out with more and more innovative apps like these to help those with challenges. Kudos and best luck..!!!

Just received a call today after installing a month back. The app is simple and to the point, while others have mentioned connection issues, I believe it to be due to network issues at either end of the call & not due to the app. I had trouble connecting only when I moved quite away from wifi router. Happy to have helped someone, I'm sure the app has made life a bit easier for hundreds of thousands of people around the world. Wishing that more people get access to incredible use of technology.

I haven't gotten a call yet, but I really like the idea. One suggestion, adding a days or time preference option to receive calls. I work 12 hour shifts Mon-Thurs and I'm not able to answer the phone. I know that a call would be redirected to someone else if I don't pick up, but that's a waste of the caller's time. If I could set it to only get calls Fri-Sun that would be great.
Just signed up yesterday and got my first call today. It feels good to help others.
replyContent:
We are pleased that you enjoyed the app. If there is anything we can do for you, just let us know at info@bemyeyes.com!
Have a wonderful day!

content: I got a call today and I tried answering and I was very exited but all it did was take me to the homepage and it kept on ringing and it would never start and now I feel bad
replyContent: We apologize for this experience. We would need to speak with you to better understand the problem you encountered. Please contact us at info@bemyeyes.com so we can help resolve this issue. Thank you.

content: What a wonderful idea. Just used it for the first time: took no time to connect. Couldn't find the thing I dropped but at least I feel better that if we both couldn't see it, it isn't just me. it's definitely hiding! I wish all health professionals and charities and other organisations knew Be My Eyes, to suggest to people. When I've given a few tries (I'm cautious about recommending to others), then I'll be spreading the word. Just wish I could volunteer. Thank you for this service!

I like this app very much. A good way to help people. If you are alone at your home or any other place and feeling bour then you should use this app to help blind people to get pleasure. I really get pleasure by helping people. In this app we can let our eyes to blind ones because eyes are a huge gift from Allah Almighty to us. We should help people to get pleasure. This is a good app. â­â­â­â­â­

You may want to review your volunteer picking algorithm. I have the app installed for several years now, and haven't yet received a single notification (even if someone picked up earlier, I'd still be able to see notifications count in the settings, but it's always "0 per week"). Even though I marked 3 languages as acceptable and am situated in quite an inhabited timezone.
I never got a call but great concept :).. i cant find a way to delete my account?

Just answered my first call today and it felt so good! I helped a vision impaired lady count money and I felt really helpful. I loved the experience and I'm looking forwards to help more people.The app is pretty simple and straightforward, as it should be. Before receiving calls, you have to active them through watching a tutorial. It does support multiple languages, which is great. It's so nice to make some difference on people's lives, as little as it may seem. Be My Eyes is a must-have.

I was kinda excited to download this because it shows how modern phones are beyond a gaming asset. I suppose the only negative thing I can say about it is that the number of volunteers is so high I will probably never get a call of my own to handle. It's at 187k/3.2m right now. ... Ok, two negative things: the tutorial video is crazy loud. If you're reading this, turn the volume down by like 50%.

It's a brilliant concept, but appears to be suffering from technical glitches. I only had two calls so far, but one of them wouldn't connect properly. Also, it would be much better if you could set different times for availability. I'm a night owl and would quite happily take calls after 9pm, but not in the morning. An option to add more than one language would be great, as well. I'm bilingual, but there is no way of adding a second language. Apart from that, I think it's great!
Very useful app.

Great concept for an app, I'm so happy! Would be great to have more features in the future to interact with the other person in the call, like maps (One time a guy needed guidance to go to a bus station and I found it hard to help as I didn't know where we where) or a chat box to send links (Another guy needed some help with setting a screen reader in his phone and details to contact 'La Once' (National Organization of Spanish blind people) ðŸ˜Š

I love the concept of the app, I love that via a simple call I can help a visually impaired person in their day to day life. Whilst I'm aware that there are many more volunteers than there are VI users, I'm a little disappointed that I have been a volunteer since April 2019 and I haven't recieved a single call. Makes me wonder if there is an issue with my account or a glitch in the algorithm or something? I just would've expected at least a couple calls by this point.

Received my first support call after installed this app for many years! Although the network connectivity was very poor, we managed to build a good teamwork within a few minutes. Feel so happy to be able to help her to find a nearby store to get a mask and get a taxi home. This experience also let me feel deeply how challenging it is without sight. I hope I can be a help for many friends in this community.
I couldn't receive col... And there there is no ring tone..( Only vibration) so sometimes dont understand.. Col get missed.. Please improve features like ring tone.. The app is ok ok..

I m glad they have such a helpful app for helping the people out! Keep up the great work ! Also , since there are soooo many volunteers, why not create a "REGIONAL" system where the volunteers would be called by blind people's who need help in their country (or even continent). That would give other volunteers more opportunity.

This app has potential but there are a few issue. Biggest being the notification system. This app should have a full screen call notification instead of just a pop up. The only reason I knew when I had a call, that I always was to late for, wasbecause I recognised the logo on my always display. Otherwise I would have never known. Fix that and this app can be great.

The creation of app is good initiative for helping blind, As a visually impaired student I have a suggestion: vh student generally need volunteers as scribers for preparing or writing assignments or exams and some time for reading. show a section for the purpose in the app could be created. Through the app the developer could try to connect the blind person and the volunteer who are ready to help academicAly, in the same city or otherwise

I love the concept of this app. But I am getting calls around the same time everyday from the same person who apparently just wants to talk. He starts with a simple task but then starts talking. It could be my inability to say "no" but I am scared of answering calls now. Might it be possible to set the amount of time of the helper's willing to share? And the person who needs help can take a guess how long it would take before the call. I realize the amount of trouble this can cause.

Simple idea but utter genius! You get an alert, shown a video link to a blind or visually impaired person. You see what they can't and talk to them. Could be which is an item of clothing or expiry date or product ingredients. Easy, simple way to make a small but significant difference to a blind person.

I very much like this app I just installed it would go and have her see my first phone call today, it was very heartwarming to be able to help the person out, and when I read the other reviews about the app and how it's useless, it kind of pisses me off because people don't realize I don't care enough to read that when a blind person needs help it connects them to ten callers so it's only when they're the first one to pick up they get connected

It's a good app, credit to the people who made it. Its a nice thing to help people who are blind. I would give this app 4 or even 5 stars but my only problem is that there are WAY more people who are volunteering to help rather then the amount of people blind. I have started since the 3rd of January and up till now, I haven gotten a single notification that someone needs help.

I've had this app for many years and have missed two calls before finally being available to answer my third. It was a great experience, unfortunately due to internet issues the screen was very blurry. I tried to report this in feedback after the call but none of the feedback avenues within the app seem to be working. I would still highly recommend downloading!

I love and cheer for what the app makes possible. It is uplifting to be able to help. However, the technical support needs to be bolstered, for instance the feedback options after the call should be more nuanced and allow open ended responses. It could help improve the call experience and improve technical prowess of the app.

Beautiful! I love the idea of this app and was just thinking something like this needs to exist for those trying to travel on our horrendous trains services and even airports, when this app was mentioned on the programme I was watching! My only concern about this being an open community app is that it leaves open for trolls. My suggestion to make it more secure would be to register a face photo and Passport page to ensure people are genuine and can be traced if they abuse this system or people.

I like the idea of the app and I'm glad it's working for the users I have however had this app installed for well over a year now and haven't received a single call. On the one hand it's great and it means there's lots of volunteers, but on the other hand it kinda feels like a waste to keep this app installed hence why I'm deleting it. I hope the app remains helpful to all users, and that they maybe add a way to see your position in q or something I don't really know but just something.

Phenomenal concept. It's great to assist and be assisted without the burden of a long process or formality. Hoping many more visually impaired can be financially stable enough to be able to connect with the service in future or that it can become something offered for free by communications companies similar to how they offer social media only plans. ðŸ» to the future

Awesome app! If you are looking at this review to see if this app is good, it's not good... It's amazing if you're looking to be a volunteer like myself, Thank You for helping people who don't have the best sight or who can't even see, they just need help with the simplest things and for you to help just for a couple minutes or even seconds YOU help someone around the world. So whoever is looking to be a volunteer try this app!

My first time answering a call and I couldn't hear the person very well and watch the video call at the same time because I wasn't able to play the sound through my speaker phone, had to keep putting the phone to my ear and off again to look at the video call. If there's any way to add a speaker phone option would work out better.

My first call caught me by surprize, I caught on quickly and know how to work a washing machine, so in mere moments somebody was washing their cloths with the expectation that the right buttons were pressed. (they were, what good is signing up unless you wish to make a positive impact on another person's life?)

Most times some other volunteer answers the call before I can. However, the couple of times that I did manage to answer, the call doesn't connect due to network issues maybe. All it shows is "connecting"and eventually the calls get disconnected. Not sure if the problem is at my end but I'm disappointed not being able to help out.

It will be good if you can group based on their expertise. Because we get many requests where the blind will require help with computer operations. If a person who is not an expert answers the call it will be of no news. Even I received a call from a blind lady to help her identify the best matching pant for a top, I am not at all good in such things. So it would be good if only a subset of volunteers with required strengths receive the help request.

Update: I have picked up a call without any problem!Thank you! I'm giving the app 5stats now! I have received three calls in a row just for today but everytime I pick up, a dialog box will pop up saying "An error occured and the call has ended". I wonder if there's something we can do to fix this. But still, kudos to the developers! Such a great app for those in need and those who wants to help them!

I so far haven't helped anyone, but I'm excited to help someone in the future and the concept is just great! I was blessed with no colour blindness or any blindness but this is such a nice and easy way to help people! Great concept, great app! Get it, doesn't cost you a cent and you can help others!!

Dont get me wrong, i love the app!, the only reason im giving it 4 stars is because since i work in other non-profit  where your main users are also helping others, you have to create strategies that feed theses users ego, and by that i mean let them know how much they are helping so they can keep coming back for more.   I think the app needs a dashboard where i can see how many calls i answered, how many minutes i spent helping the app main users.  Otherwise is always a great pleasure to help and itÂ´s so satisfying.!

Doesn't allow you to answer from locked phone (Moto g7), unlike normal calls. I've missed 3 calls in the year that I've had this installed, simply because nothing at all shows on screen, just my usual black locked screen, despite ringing. I have to unlock my phone using the pin...which takes time, and by then I've missed it. Really disappointing
wonderful idea. But can't attend the call .

A simple yet very kind concept, well implemented, providing great opportunities for someone with reasonable eyesight (like me) to help someone who would like and value that assistance. Such is the joy and power of kindness that I feel happier to be able to help in often simple yet appreciated ways; and also to learn from and marvel at the very different perspectives and rich lives of blind and partially sighted people, both through the individual connections and the amazing "podcast" interviews.

Hiya Went to send a suggestion but it only directs you to share the app. Thought I'd write it here. I think it would be great to have an option of more than one language for people who are bilingual + That's all. Otherwise a brilliant app and brilliant idea

Nice app! It would be great if the helper could see beforehand which language the caller is set on, because I usually don't know which language that I have put into the app should I start with and if I speak a foreign language the person on the other side is usually unsure what is going on.

It worked perfectly with me I had no problem with the other person about internet or call disconnecting, we end up by solving the problem that he had together . I was so happy to talk to him and help . But the problem is that I have never received a call since that day, its been now more than 5 months and Im updating the app and everything but nothing :(

This is the real experience behind support in the blind community and Making connections I never knew was possible! So far I have had 4 experiences with calls. My latest one was sadly answered quicker by someone else. On my first support call, the person was looking to ensure they looked good for a date. Not only could I say she was stunning but I was also in the meeting with an Ojibwe Alder who is then able to talk about body positivity and loving ourselves in our own skin. 5 stars

I love this app in general. I find the concept of helping people, with them and I having access to this app easily, is honestly genius. However, I use this app for volunteer work in a foundation. The one thing I would appreciate is the option to record the call, or at least document the duration of the call. Apart from the actual call itself, the option to evidence the call would be a very helpful feature.

Uhm, hi good day! I suggest to improve this application by letting the blind to choose him/her assistance. Coz some girls and boys is not comfortable talking with a guy or a girl, especially when the blind is talking about girl things or boy things so that the blind can be comfortable with the volunteers. Thank you
A wonderful development, great initiative and I'm impressed by whoever came up with the idea of this app. Hope they all have a beautiful day everyday.

I've had this app for a month or so, and I've not been able to help anyone. The population of volunteers grows faster than the population of blind people in the app. It'd be nice to see how many blind and volunteers are connected at the same time, to evaluate if there's or not need of having the app running.

Amazing! The fact that I could help someone I didn't know, so overwhelms me. This has become a permanent fixture on all phones going forward. What a miraculous app. As far as I am concerned, this should be preinstalled on every phone instead of the likes of Facebook.

It is really overwhelming that the producer of this app thinks about the sake of blind people... Besides on the bad people in the world, there are still good people that can help the most. Especially people with disabilities... Through this telecommunicatoon, people worldwide know how to value the meaning of friendship and caress. May God continue to bless the people with disabilitiess safety!

A great idea, but poor follow up. I have had this app for over a year now, I have received total of 2 calls. It is a shame that there is such an imbalance between the number of volunteers and visually impaired people. This app could change the world for a lot of people from especially less developed countries, including my own. I find it difficult to understand how the same people who had the idea to create such an amazing app, does absolutely nothing to improve their app and awareness... SHAME

Excellent idea, terrible implementation. This app makes more connection attempts than probably the 10 random apps combined. Even before doing anything with it, and without running it, it's CONSTANTLY trying to contact Facebook & Google & who knows what else. It has 6 trackers encoded , so it seems it just clickbait for people who want to help others, instead of helping they mine your data.uninstall it and be vigilant.Privacy allways matters.

This apps is very good,,you can ask whatever question you want and they will answers,,you also can ask them to read and they'll read perfectly and nicely,,oh btw the replier is not a robot,it's human,when we want to ask something,,it almost like we're in video call but they'll not show our face,,i reallyÂ² love this appsðŸ’—ðŸ˜ i wanna say a lot of thanks for those who created this appsðŸ˜†
The phone keeps ringing even if the call is answered by others volunteer.The app needs to be modified.

It's awesome how you can help for free in less than a minute. Knowing you can do something to help people in need around the globe is just so awesome. The camera is clear, so are the voices. This is just such a good application. I was so delighted to be able to help and make a difference in blind people's everyday tasks. Thank you so much Be My Eyes team and I really hope everybody downloads this app!

Hey, this to give a tiny winy suggestion. Many people are bilingual,let alone multi-lingual. If the app can have an option of choosing more than 1 language, it'll make reaching out for the people in need more feasible.
Amazing in love with this!

What a great idea for an app. One recommendation I have is to have a setting for helpers so they can set their availability to answer calls, just incase some people work backshifts, that way they can still help but there isn't the risk of this app ringing for them if they forget to silence or Do Not Disturb mode their phone!

This is an update on my review, Until now I have only received one call that was the one which dropped... since then nothing. :( I just received a call from someone who most likely needed help but when I answered the call it didn't connect, and the call dropped. I have had the application installed for a while now... this was my first call. I really want to help... the 3 stars is for your great initiative... when I successful help someone using it I will increase your rating.
Couldn't answer the call as it said "allow microphone access" which is on already and it didn't ring , plz fix it for the app to be helpful

I took my first call today, after two months of downloading the app. It was a lady from England and I got very exited! The camera quality wasn't the best, but we managed to have a good interaction. She needed me to check on expiration dates for some cookies. It was an undescribable feeling that I felt after the call was over. I love this app and would like to help more people.

although the concept is amazing there is such a larger ratio of volenteers to users. I have had the app installed for weeks ans today I recieved my first call I jumped at the chance to answer and did just was quickly met with male genitalia less then 10 seconds into the call. I repirted the caller and I recieved a email saying the person had been blocked so they are clearly very pro active but I dont really want it installed any more.
I think this app is brilliant. I have had one opportunity to assist so far . But I have missed so many. The app needs a distinct loud ring tone. It is so quiet on my phone I often miss the alert.

Fantastic idea and good implementation: there are way more volunteers than people who need to be helped, so you may not receive any calls. I had the privilege of helping someone verify their grocery bill and will be keeping this app in case I get the opportunity to help again.

Great idea, fine app, but I think they should have said that there is 4.5 million volunteer helpers and only like 420 thousand people who sometimes ask for help, so you're hardly ever asked to help. I think they should have said that before you give your email and make a password etc. And I think it drains a little battery.

love the idea and the app. just received my first call, and the only fault I can point out is I wish there was a callback option. I had to answer the door and said i would call her back to finish our call, only to realize I couldn't.
Amazing app. I helped someone on the other side of the world turn their washing machine on. I sat down and cried with happiness afterwards!
A real feel good app, I love being able to help others. Have used this a few times now as someones eyes. The users are always polite and friendly. I get excited when the app starts ringing.

I usually don't write reviews, but for this app, I just have to write one. I love this. It's perfect if you want to help someone. At first, I was apprehensive if I'd really be able to help and not, well, screw things up. But after answering a few calls, I've found that my worries were unfounded. The tasks were fairly simple. It was a satisfying experience. Kudos to the people that made this app. You all have my respect.

I think thats a really very good initiative for the people who are blind and its also very great app for the people who are willing to help them as this type of little change can bring something great and as i can see that there are more people who want to help then the one who needs help which clearly determine that there is humanity alive somewhere. Wonderful creaters hats off.ðŸ‘ðŸ»

I love the concept of the app but I have a doubt that if I get a call in night it will just wake me up. So please add a feature in which you can select the time that you will be available in and can help another visualy impaired person.
Can't answer any calls anymore, the "trying to answer the call" screen never disappears.

Brilliant concept. I didn't get calls initially but I kept the app. I got my first call after 2 months or so. Now I it has been close to a year now I have been using this app and now I get a call almost everyday. I have been able to help fellow brothers and sisters thanks to this beautiful app. Kudos to the team.

I don't know how real the visually impaired people on this app are. Today I got a call from a person with his rear camera on and I could very clearly see there were a lot of visually active people around him in that they were all moving freely in a field doing normal activities easily, I don't know how to explain it but none of them were blind, they were all present within a two arm distance of the caller. Was the caller not blind? Couldn't he have taken their help? Don't think I'll answer now
Got a call and it won't connect
replyContent: Hi, thank you for volunteering! Connection issues can occur due to many reasons, but could you please send us more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can fix the problem? Thank you!

content: Let's not talk about the Software side! This is a great idea and when you come to think that it's been build completely to benefit someone else in need!!!! Great job! Absolutely loving the app and the idea! Everytime when I get a call my heart gets filled mich happiness!

Excellent idea and so good for not just the caller but the volunteer too. In terms of feelings of fullfillment and usefulness etc certainly but also one of being connected to someone else in times of loneliness etc.. or just wanting to connect. I'm not suggesting people use the platform as a samaritans line but i guess were yet to see where it goes from here. Quite exciting. Especially waiting for my 1st call. Thankyou for the chance to try and be a "growgiver"as Anthony Robins rightly puts it.

Just registered and waiting for my first call. The idea is brilliant, I've seen this app in an YouTube ad and decided I just have to be a part of such and heartwarming initiative. The app itself is designed well, clean and practical. An ABSOLUTE must have.

downloaded the app yesterday and got a call the next day! it was an old man trying to figure out what color 2 of his shirts are. it was a quick one although we did have to figure out how to move the phone camera a bit. i used to work at a call center company so i was very familiar with how to help people in need. this is a good app to help people

I downloaded this app months ago, or late last year and have been waiting for a call since then. I got my first call just now but unfortunately I couldn't speak Spanish and the person that needed help only spoke Spanish. I badly wanted to help, and I was so excited to help too. I hope there would be a feature where in they could match the caller to the people who can speak the language. :( really sad I couldn't help and I feel guilty now too. Hoping this would be improved!

I am new to this app, and I think that a good improvment could be the possibility of helping in two or more different lenguages, fir example, I speal both spanish and english fluently, and I can only choose one to help, so yeah, that could be a good update to this fantastic app

The very first screen asks you too agree to the privacy policy and terms of service, but it wouldn't let me click any links to read these, the only button in the screen was "I agree". But how can I agree without even being given the options l to read it.

Its an amazing app, i however have 1 concern, i sorta have phone anxiety, a call made my heart beat fast, and i did a call testing. The loud beeping/ vibrating sent me in a bit of a panic. If possible please let us have the options to make it less vibrating, or possibly just a little tiny ping. Thank you
I'd get a call once in a while but the call would never connect.
replyContent: Hi, we apologize for any issue you might be having! Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our customer support at info@bemyeyes.com? We'll get you up and running.

content: This is an amazing application. It helps the blind people and makes their work easier. You help people in need just by answering some of their questions on a video call. You are helping humanity by this gesture of kindness. It's a nice app and has good features.

Issue with the calls. While the concept is great, I have received 4 calls so far and I was unable to answer any of them. The buttons on the screen were not working whatsoever! I really want to be able to help but it's pointless for me to keep this app if I can't use it :(

I answered a Chinese speaker's call today but the other end never heard my voice for unknown reason. The video call then stop working as it freezes at one point and became black screen. I just hope that the person got the help they needed, maybe it's a bug to do with this app, but I hope not.

Im a volunteer, and while ive only had a couple calls in the year ive had bme it was easy to use and understand and i was easily able to help blind callers with whatever task they needed sited help with. If i were to have a complaint is that i wish i got called more haha. As im writing this theres currently on average of 17 volunteers to every blind user which is awesome. Im glad that users are able to connect with so many ppl and have options if one volunteer is busy and cant answer

This app has a very good cause, one thing I would add are qualities, like if a volunteer is trained and experienced in a certain field he or she can help in that field professionally. It could also help you make friends with people who share your interests

Perhaps the most satisfying app I have. One way that I could be of help. I cannot tell you how content you feel when you are of some use to someone via this app. Reduced the stars as i see blind folks are not even using it. 3L users only. Can we not undertake initiatives that use volunteers to increase usage of this app?
Such a wonderful idea. I leave it logged in when I'm in the kitchen pottering around and I've already had my first call. I helped a partially sighted man from Sheffield read his mail.

I honestly would love to give this app 5 stars. But the truth is I've installed it and registered for help over 2 years ago and I never received any request of assistance. I set the language as Italian cause that's the language I'm more comfortable with. Kind of disappointed :-/

Would love to hear from support as I had a technical issue with a call and at the end I could only thumbs up the call rather than report the issue and when I went to press "send us feedback" in the actual app it won't click when every other button works.

Not sure if this app is working properly. Love the concept but had one call that I couldn't connect to only and nothing else so I really hope it will be remedied so volunteers and those needing help will be assisted.

Got my first call today. First time for me and the person I was helping. Audio was good and picture was sharp. I was able to help, exchange pleasantries and finish the interaction in just a couple of minutes. It was a good feeling to help someone, plus it was so easy.

Be My Eyes is a brilliant application for individuals that have visual impairments. I had recently answered my first call to an individual that wanted to know the readings of a stationary bike. I'm glad to have assisted.
The developer is a smart dude. Love the app, excellent experience with call from anywhere in the world. But one thing, need an update to add more languages. I speak English n Arabic.

we need to make sure this app is spread far and wide. The number of blind compared to the volunteers is low so you aren't harassed but when you do get that call and manage to help it gives you a huge smile for the rest of the day knowing you have done good.

Great ad. This App had the first ad in years that i was interested in watching. Im glad, i can help someone out who needs help. Hell, maybe ill need help from this app someday. What a wonderful idea and thanks to everyone helping.

The only reason I am giving 4 stars to this is because there is no option to choose more than one language of interaction/support. Although I can converse in Kannada, Hindi and English, I can only choose one language in the settings.

I want to give it 4 stars just because they are helping others who are blind and are trying to make thier life much more easier. But because of some stangers if he gets in problem then nobody will help him except the blind person. But the app is really good and helpfull!

When the Android version of this finally appeared, I was excited to have a chance to help vision-impaired people in such an ingenious way. (It also seemed to make sense for the developers to stop focusing exclusively on Apple ownersâ€”who are, in my experience, more likely to be preoccupied with style and status than "the rest of us" are.) However, after having it installed for months, and not getting a single help request, I'm giving up. I'm glad the volunteer response has been so overwhelmingâ€”better that than too fewâ€”but there's also something to be said for, you know, actually getting to help someone sometime..?

This is an amazing and innovative app. If you have the time to spare then you can genuinely make a difference to someone who is sight impaired. You're helping people with everyday tasks, which really makes you appreciate what you have. Beneficial for both parties.
This is an amazing app for the visually disabled. Hatsoff to the people who ideated it and created it. I have been on this just 14 days and already had the chance to help 2 wonderful ladies.

Love the app, but several times the video quality is not clear enough to read out the text other person is asking for, so please fix that, or it is an internet issue, sorry but fix it if it's from your end.
Nice app. waited for days and i still don't understand why i haven't recieved my first call yet.

My experience on this app has been humbling to say the least... I've been able to attend quite a few calls and do my bit to help the ones in need! My congratulations to the team that developed this app! Absolutely brilliant initiative!

I love the idea of the app and it's really lovely that someone came up with it at all but I've never received a call from anyone needing help and I've had it for just under a year. While I'm glad that there are far more sighted people to help than people who need it, it does mean that I can't give the full 5 stars I want to since I haven't experienced all aspects of the app.

Sound doesn't work. I got one call and it hung up immediately. Sending feedback doesn't work - WhatsApp was trying to send something (not sure what) and it asked me for a contact, instead of having the contact pre-filled and letting me write the content. Xiaomi Mi 10 Lite.

It was amazing untill several updates came and ruined everything. EVERYTIME I receive a call and I answer it, the call ends immediately with this damn error of " An unknown error occurred." Fix it for God's sake! My device is Mi Note 10, android version 11

Oh God, I could not have anticipated the joy this would be. It works seamless and the app tries pairing up geographically which helps everyone better understand and be able to help each other. The experience itself is often short, but leaves you feeling incredibly wholesome for far longer

Just signed up yesterday and got my first call today. Its amazing how you can help someone via technology these days. Quality of signal and camara capabilities could pose a problem bit other than that it went down smoothly.
the idea of the application is amazing, but I can not answer any call, the app get stuck on "trying to answer the call" screen please fix this issue.

I haven't had the chance to answer a call yet, but for some reason EVERY TIME I open any app BME opens instead, for no apparent reason. This never happened with any other apps and only happens with this, I'm not sure why but it's really annoying
Thank you, be my eyes is very interesting!
Amazing cool app that helps people all over the world. It's really impressive and cool and most important helpful to lend your eyes out to someone who just can't see. I love it.

One of the greatest humanitarian projects I have come across. I recently helped a blind woman in Maryland identify the bills in her wallet and it was a great and rewarding interaction. It's so simple to make someone else's day easier and better.

Had the chance to answer a call today, and felt so rewarding to be able help someone even in just little ways. At first the connection was kinda laggy but eventually it went well. Was able to help someone even if it's just online. Hope you keep up this good work and so far had no other issues with the app.
Just used to it to help out. Something as small as figuring out which wallet card is which. It's super simple to use and takes a minute or two of your time. Well done devs!

I love this initiative. BUT, I tapped through the post-call review much too quickly and accidentally flagged it as negative... How do I change that. I do not want to leave a negative review of a caller that was perfect and genuine. Please help.

I think it's a brilliant tool to help people. Such an innovative approach to be there for someone even if its simple as picking an apple for them. I have just joined however looking forward to my first help. I hope I'm available for the call. I work in health care and I know the struggle.

I just helped an elderly couple with registration and I never felt so alive and satisfied ever before in my life you are doing an amazing job keep it up. Just a suggestion have a multi language registration process, so I can help as many people I can

This is by far one of the best humanitarian apps out there, actually helpful, and should be aggressively publicized, because there's actually a lot of people who could use a helping hand, or in this case, some helping sight.
Unresponsive App - when trying to respond to a call, the app responds with "please wait" and absolutely nothing else happens. Great idea, but not so much if the tech lets it down.

Gr8 app!! One Feedback - There are lot of blind people require voluntary writer for their exams. People are taking huge money from them for this social work. Check if you can add this feature in app. It will be a great help.

Why Cant I set a time up for when people call through. My phone was getting a call from the app at 3 in the morning and to be honest I don't want to be woken up even if it is to help someone. Let someone else who is awake answer the call. Anyway I need to put settings on this I can't see how and don't want to be woken up in the middle of night. Thanks great idea though
replyContent: Hello, sorry you had this experience. Yet, we match based on language and time zone - meaning we only contact volunteers during their daytime hours.  The standard settings only allow you to receive calls between 8am and 9pm (08:00-21:00) in your local time zone by default. You can contact us at info@bemyeyes.com if you need further assistance.

content: I'm so happy that this kind of thing exists. My Dad was completely blind, and as he passed away in '95 there wasn't anything like this, but I know it would have been a massive help to him. The fact that random strangers are willing and able to give their time to help others in need is just fantastic, and it gives me hope for humanity.
What an amazing use of technology! Super easy to use. Tons of volunteers so the call volume is low but hopefully this app gets more exposure soon so we can help more people who need it!
I think this is s brilliant idea, but I've received two calls in (what feels like) a year and both times I couldn't answer. It just says "trying to answer" but never does.
I tried to send a feedback but it sent me to the share menu it seems. Also the test call is not working with my bluethooth headset, but it worked on the speakers. Great concept/idea!
The app is perfect! But one of the blind person told me, the app doesn't allow him to make too many calls. As he is blind he needs help complete day
Lately I've been receiving a lot of calls more then the usual calls. All of them are just erreurs . I mean they are not real calls. I dont know how this could happen . Hope u fix yhis asap
This app is a really nice idea. One thing that would make it 5 stars is an option to activate/deactivate calls, so I can clock out when busy.
Verry verry essential app which need to download to every cell phoneðŸ˜

I love the app the volunteers are so helpfull to me and i Was resently dignosed with rp (retanytis pigmontosa) and i will high recommend the app to all my blind and vishal inperd friend and i use the app for the ferst time today i needed help with checking the expiry date on some thing and i would love it if u could put a feach a in for it to be easyer if u want content with a spsific volunteer please ðŸ˜Š

Love the app. Just wish more people who are blind knew how to get the app. Some of the volunteers should be removed for being enactive for more that 2 weeks just so others can use their space to help others.
Amazing app! I was so excited when I got my first call, and I felt absolutely elated after helping my caller. The creator of this app is a genius!
The only reason I won't give this app 5 stars is because when I try to give feedback on my call, the Problem button doesn't work but the Good button does, which is disingenuous.
A good update would be to have a button that somehow puts you in a "front line" for getting calls. Let's say I got some free time and I would be glad to use it to help people.
Missed a call few days after registering, however another call came through some days after and I was able to assist the caller, felt good to be able to do that from half the globe.

Hi I am from pakistan and I am blind person. This app is very useful. Specially, the specialised help system is fine we can contact with Google and Microsoft to improve our accessibility apps. I love this app very much. You have right to get 5 stars. That's why I give you five star

Magnificent idea Hope to add more options for more specification to make the people who needs help more comfortable Like gender even helper or requester, geographic area, age range As this may give both parts of the call more relieved and not being shy specifically girls as they have more private needs which men might not be able to understand or fulfill

This is a wonderful service, and I hope most sighted people are able and willing to help here. It seems like they are, as I've gotten two calls in the time I've used the app, and had a lovely time providing aid to a blind person.
I love it! Gives me so much joy to do a good deed.
Would be better if I could specify the times I could help out.
Amazing app! Only thing missing is the ability for volunteers to change their availability, hopefully this is coming in the future.

I installed this app thinking I could help someone in need, and I have helped people before in this aop. Today I received a call from somebody, who asked me how old I am, if I am married etc.. I definitely dont think that person was blind. Is there any way you guys could confirm the other party is actually blind?
I grew up with special people and i know the difficulties they face in life. I appreciate the app and the tutorial was very nice, simple, informative. Hope we can all help each other

I think this is a great app! Although it may be a good idea to add the option to choose whether you receive messages/calls only so people who may experience phone anxiety can also help out as much as possible.

Thanks to the creators will always be here if anyone needs my help. maybe i'm not updated but how do blind people navigate their phone? i used Android talkback. wasn't easy. still nice to create value for impaired people. ðŸ‘ðŸ¼
Just took my first call for help and only had the app installed a couple of days. Wow, really useful app and the caller just needed 30 seconds of my time and I'm so pleased I could help

Got my first call today I answered but was black screen and no audio coming through either. I had a good connection too. I don't know what the problem was but I'm gutted I hope they got the help :( xx
Disappointed with this, excellent concept, but each time someone calls and I try to pick up the call, the call ends abruptly showing an error has occurred
Such a brilliant app to assist the blind or partially blind. I would like more calls assigned to me. These acts of kindness warm my heart.
I think this is a helpful app for the blind. It can help blind people a lot and can make a great change in thier lives. With the help of this app they can be helped with many things.
Great app, the initiative to help individuals requiring visual assistance is incredible. Gives you an excellent feeling when you can genuinely help someone.
I really recommend this app to all. Sighted people can help blind people become even more independent through technology. What's not to love about it?

Review as a volunteer : I'm happy to be able to help even in the smallest things. As for the app love the option to turn on the flashlight. Easy to use,Very user-friendly. Can help people in multiple languages! Just grateful for this app

A great app, as a volunteer it really makes me feel how can i influence positively in few minutes of my time when helping someone somewhere in the world, certainly it's a precious experience for everyone. Thank you
I've answered a couple of calls in a month after months of silence. Very happy to know it works! Both times, I answered a call asking me to help read some setting off a gadget.
Dear Sir, I received a call little bite time before but when I clicked on receiving call, it gave message "error in call" Kindly check what's problem that I could not receive call properly
Its an awsome app, i was already able to help someone. However I feel like the app is poorly built and has a weak backend.

Never been called. I've had the app for 15 months now and not heard a peep. Doing something wrong maybe? I don't keep the app open at all times but that doesn't stop push notifications coming through on it. Update, coming on to 2 full years and still no call. Is it advertised enough to those who need it?
I just helped a couple who were having an issue with their laptop. It was great I could see their laptop screen and was able to tell them what needed it was great. Everyone should download this app!

I received a call and the caller wanted to know tge uses of the app but his camera wasn't working well and then the call ended suddenly ðŸ˜• I was really disappointed I recommend sending the volunteers an idea about the view of the other one when they call.
It felt really good when you helped a blind person. This app deserves more than a gazillion stars!!!
Amazing idea for an app. So helpful. The app just sits on my phone until someone calls. Feels great to be able to help someone with simple things that we take for granted.

I got my first call a few days after I installed the app. I accepted the call but it would not connect . It tried to connect for a few minutes and then stopped . After that I tried to go into the app to see what was wrong but the app would not open either.
I got two calls, but I couldn't get my caller because the system is unstable. Always an error occurres. Maybe you can work on this issue. Otherwise it is a good idea

I didnt answer a call yet but the idea behind this app is awesome and really good job and thank you to the creators I loved your ideas and if you could do some other apps for the people with the hearing disability it will be really good

great application to help others but the 2 times I received calls I got disconnected and have server error , not to mention I can barely log to the application every time Hope to fix it soon to be able

Beautiful App. Probably the best idea ever since the invention of internet. So far I only got to answer one call and it made my day. Something so simple and so extremely useful. Thank you for making that happen. â¤
Brilliant idea. There is a 15:1 (volunteers:blind) ratio now, so tell your blind friends all about it.
Really love this app, is very functional for blind people, and I'm glad to be a volunteer for this good reason. I downloaded the app yesterday and today I had my first request ðŸ™ŒðŸ»
This concept is a perfect solution to all people that are blind and you don't have to be a speacilist to help someone but there are so many volunteers that you barely get a call most of the time.
Very simple to use app. Dont find it disturbing or intrusive. Receive maybe 1 call in 2/3 days that to which gets responded by others faster than. Wonderful initiative
Just got my first call and I answered but there was just a message for a few minutes saying trying to connect. I couldn't hear anyone. I hope the person was able to find help anyway.
I just saw the ad on YouTube. I haven't downloaded/used the app yet. I'm only rating it 5-stars because of the concept and it's brilliant. Cheers to the developers. Great work.
Have tried answering a handful of calls and they never connect. Just spins forever.

Wonderful app. I have only received one call because there are so many volunteers. But that's a good thing, so many people willing to take a few minutes out of their day to help a stranger. There is still a lot of good in this world :)

I know it's impossible to tell if the person calling is actually visually impaired but please try to do set a feedback system where we can tell if the person really needed that app or was using it for kicks

the idea is beautiful, i just installed 5 minutes ago so i dont yet have experience with it but i have a suggestion. i cant find a way to tell when you are available. it would be nice to say what days and hours of that day you are most likely to pick up your phone.

If u don't give five stars to this app, you can't give 5 stars to any other app. It's helping a lot of people. It's an amazing feeling to help someone in need. Thank you so much "Be my eyes" team of developers. ðŸ¤— Btw there is a minor connection problem when internet speed is a little low. Please fix that.
Great app. I feel that it helps me as much as a volunteer as it helps the clients.
Nice concept. Please add a feature to share screen. Sometimes they ask for Captcha code while using the same phone. There are technical glitches at time but overall a nice application.
I've been a member since Nov 15, 2020 and I still haven't received a call. It's Jan 2022.
replyContent: Hi! Since we have so many wonderful volunteers, it can often take a while for people to receive their first calls. We hope a call comes in soon for you!

replyContent: Hello Paula, we have a strict policy regarding misuse. If you ever experience misuse or abuse from the other caller, you can report it immediately after the call. Your feedback is not shared with the other part. We handle all abuse reports with close attention. Users who break our Terms of service will be blocked from the Be My Eyes community.

I just answered my first call as a volunteer. The request was so simple: A 
lady wanted help navigating to the next page on a website, which we were 
able to quickly resolved together. I didn't save anyone's life, I didn't 
cure cancer, but hearing her laugh and say "thank you!" when we got to the 
next page made me feel like a hero. I have the biggest smile on my face 
right now for making this small difference in someone's day. God bless the 
creators of this app. You've helped enrich the lives of so many people.

Bring a sighted user I love being helpful and it is the best app, I've only 
received one call so far and it was a pleasant one. However i do wish there 
was a option, in say a future update where you can select available or 
unavailable. In a video I saw which got me excited to try this app it 
states that if during the middle of the night it would connect a visually 
impaired individual in the UK. Which likely the best avenue. However in my 
situation I work 12 hour days and 12 hour graveyard shifts rotating each 
week, so having a option to say I'm available now or certain times during 
the day or night. Would be useful for me. I suppose if there are enough 
users it hardly matters. Just my two cents.

A wonderful app!! Truly lovely â¤ï¸ but I must say, there really should be an a option to be able to input your availability, so that it can be programmed to call you during hours you are actually available. I work full time so it would be nice to be able to say the hours that I'm at home. Plus the app can the hone in the calls on the people most likely to respond :)

I am a volunteer. I was playing music from my phone when someone called and 
when I answered I turned the music off. The thing is every time I opened 
the Be My Eyes app, the music would come back on. I am not sure what 
happened and the person had to disconnect. I hope they found the help they 
needed. I also wish that hadn't happened. Do y'all have any advice to 
prevent that from happening?

This is probably the best idea for an app. I like to help people and this

I hardly review apps, but this is simply the best app available on the Play

aspect would be to flag that you're unavailable, it doesn't personally 
affect me, but I can imagine certain people and their inconsistent work 
shifts this would be beneficial to them.

Wonderful idea. I wish the app had a ringer volume control, I haven't heard

Maybe a history screen too? The ratio of volunteers to those being served

THE BEST APP IN PLAY STORE! I don't think my words can describe the app. 
This app is like the future. It helps a ton to the blind people. The 
Volunteer service is superb! The developers are very creative to come upon 
app like these. Seriously Really need to appreciate this app.

I've been signed up for a while and got my first call today. Got to help a 
man who got turned around guided back home. Kindness costs nothing and it's 
just another reason I love this app. Don't be discouraged if it takes a 
while to get a call. When you do, it's all worth it

Im a visually impaired person. This app has saved my life on at least 2 occassions. Once running a new to me trail the person helped guide me back to my meeting spot. This morning i was at the store. I couldn't read a food label or find a person there to help me. I have some serious food allergies. The person read the label to me and when i didnt know one the person with her goggled it. Thus knew i couldnt safely eat it or id need to use my epipen. Thank you for having this available. Thank you to the people who are willing to be my eyes. <3

I love the app. My sole criticism is that I ONLY want notifications when 
someone wants a helper. I DO NOT want notifications for a video or blog 
post that the app creators wish to share. At a minimum, there should be a 
setting allowing you to choose this. For now, I can't turn off 
notifications, because that is the only way I can be helpful, but I haven't 
gotten a notification for someone needing help the whole time I've had the 
app on Android. I've only received notifications to watch videos and read 
stories about the service. I helped several times when I has the app on my 
Apple device.

Love the app, the concept, everything. I am a sighted volunteer. And I am 
Pentalingual. However, it appears I can only choose one primary language? 
I'd love to be able to choose all 5 that I speak. Please bring an update 
for this. For now, I've chosen a non-English language since it appears 
English volunteers are in abundance.

I am a sighted volunteer. In the time I have been on this app I have had 
two calls. It was a great feeling being able to help someone. Both ladies 
that I helped were friendly, gracious and grateful. My first call was to 
help someone reading a temperature gauge. And the second call was helping 
an elderly lady to set the settings on her washing machine. Took a little 
bit of time but we did it. She then asked me where I was, and told me where 
she was. And we ended up being several provinces away from each other. We 
talked about different things and had a really nice little chat about the 
different places we lived and of course the very Canadian weather, the 
wildfires over where she lives, and in general how wonderful this app was 
for not only helping people but connecting people. She was so very thankful 
and in the end it was like talking to an old friend across the distance of 
several provinces. For the few minutes it took out of my busy day to help 
them with theirs this is a great thing..

This is an exceptional idea for an app. It's also well executed overall. 
The app works as advertised, and the selection of languages impressed me (I 
was pleasantly surprised to see even Esperanto included!). The only 
downside is the extreme rarity of receiving a call as a volunteer. It seems 
new volunteers often get a call within the first day - probably to keep 
them interested - but after that calls are few and far between. I received 
one call on my first day, but it was answered by another volunteer before I 
could get it. After that I received no calls for a couple weeks despite 
keeping the app running 24/7. Yesterday I finally received another call, 
which I answered. It seems much more promotion among the blind/vision 
impaired community is needed to help even out the numbers and so that even 
more people can be helped. Still, the app is an amazing resource for those 
who use it, and I'll keep it installed for those rare times when I may be 
available to assist quicker than anyone else. As someone who routinely 
relies on help from others due to health issues, it's nice to be able to 
help others once in awhile, too.

New to the "Be My Eyes" app, so haven't received a call yet, but giving the 
concept five stars and then some! As a volunteer my only complaint, like 
many others listed, is that we cannot set our own call times. For instance, 
the app calls most people during the volunteer's daylight hours from 8 an 
to 9 pm...rather than the volunteer's "awake and available" hours. So for 
instance, if a blind user in the US needs assistance and in their own time 
zone it is 2:00 am in the morning...it would be considered the middle of 
the night for most volunteers in the US. So instead of a volunteer in the 
US getting a call, the call would be routed to volunteers on the other side 
of the world who would normally be awake in the "daytime hours". My 
problem, as a volunteer, is that I am a night person in the US. So calls 
may be routed to me during the day when I am sleeping and unavailable to 
respond. And calls from the other side of the world won't come to me when I 
am awake at night, because of the "only call in day hours from 8 am to 9 
pm" policy. So I may never get to respond to calls for help, but I am 
willing and able! I look forward to being of assistance. I can usually 
accept calls from 2:00 PM to 7:00 am Pacific Standard Time, and would love 
to be a voice in the night to help others! Just make the app able to allow 
users to set their own availability and then I'd give 10 stars if I could! 
Please add this option to the development of the app? The only other issue 
I can see a problem with is that a user is not supposed to put medical info 
or medication info out to a volunteer and volunteers are asked not to help 
with such. On the one hand....I can understand this, as that could be a 
serious liability for developers and volunteers to take on, if something 
were to go wrong. And there ARE actually bad people out there who could do 
harm to others in regards to medication taking. But on the other hand, if I 
were blind and taking medications I would certainly want to know that there 
was someone in the middle of the night that could help me with such....for 
instance, if I dropped my medications and needed help sorting them again, 
or if I needed help reading a prescription label for correct dosage or even 
to relabel it in Braille, or to read safety precautions on over the counter 
medications, to tell me if a medication was expired before taking it. So 
it's got it's good points and bad, there's no way around that really except 
to make the rule of not asking for help with such and not giving help on 
such, but that's unfortunate. Other than those two things.....what a GREAT 
service the inventer/developer has offered to world. Your generous heart is 
a rare kindness and I, for one, thank you for your foresight and altruism. 
*HUGS*

Already received two calls from people needing assistance. I'll be honest, 
it's such a fulfilling feeling knowing not only that you helped someone 
when they really needed it, but that by helping them you instill the 
confidence in them that there are always those willing to lend a hand. I 
will keep this app on every device I ever own, and promote it as long as my 
voice will allow. With all the games and stupid rinky-dink apps out there, 
it's infinitely rewarding to have one that actually and directly effects 
people who need help. All the kudos I have go to the developers.

I'm totally blind and just used Be My Eyes successfully for the first time. I've tried it before but my Internet was never good enough. I have a different phone and carrier now, so I tried it again. My computer seemed frozen, and my screen reader wouldn't talk at all. I'm alone, so I installed Be My Eyes, called a volunteer and asked what it was doing. She confirmed that it was frozen and not responding at all, so I was able to restart it and get things going again. I had a wonderful experience using it and will definitely keep it installed! I'm glad so many volunteers are willing to help!

A great idea, and I'm glad it's so successful!

It essentially shows the helper live video asking for help with a task; Which button on the remote is Input? Is this is blue or green? Is this a cigarette lighter or a flash drive?  bemyeyes is good. please support it.

I think the idea of this app is really good! But there is a problem that, i got my first call after weeks and what happened in that, really moved me. First of all i was feeling shy before picking up the call but after waiting for a few seconds i picked up the call. At first the video streaming was not good but after that it got stable. It was a man who was showing signs from his hand held in front of back camera of phone. I thought that he was trying to say something but after that he he picked up another phone and unlocked it and went to the messages app and typed "fu*k u" . That was really a bad experience i mean a person is answering you thinking that that he is going to help you but what he gets in return? A prank caller just may be checking the application? Ridiculous really!
The app itself is a great app, but I wish a blind person could write (via audio) and you could answer in a text, which then will be read out loud. I believe that sistem could help a lot also.

It's a way to make a difference; sure it may be in a small way...at least it may seem small to you...until you hear the gratitude in there voice when they say thanks/thank you for your help/and the list goes on.  The climate in the US related to political things has this country the most divided in my lifetime; so WHY NOT take a moment to help someone...you never know how big or small, sorry for the rant ppl I am just passionate about focusing on good and positive things. So, get off social media once and while and use this app. It takes so little space. I hope this app keeps growing and surpasses every goal the developer/creators had. Currently there are approximately 60 thousand non-sighted/impaired sighted individuals on this app and approximately 800 thousand sighted ppl. I hope it continues to evolve to help ppl even more people and in more ways. An unsolicited plug for this app, to stop what you're doing and download it. And ppl out there, PLEASE volunteer in your community as well!  Hats off to the creators and developers of this app! The world needs more positivity and ways to help fellow man.

replyContent: Hello Jennifer, since we have 3+ million volunteers, it might take time to get a call. All we can ask for is your patience, we hope you will catch a call quite soon. For those that haven't noticed yet, blind and visually impaired people are more and more able to use smartphones or tablets through features like apple's voice over. replyContent: Hello, we have a strict policy regarding misuse. If you ever experience misuse or abuse from the other caller, you can report it immediately after the call.
